title: jenny's cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter in pan. Blend in flour and stir. Stir in broth and simmer 2 minutes. Add milk and half and half, stirring constantly until thickened. Do not boil. Add crab meat. Add salt and pepper to taste. Makes 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions and spread over pecans and coconut.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oven chicken
directions: Place a layer of chicken in a casserole dish.
Salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Repeat until all chicken is used.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine soup and milk and heat below boiling point.
Pour over chicken.
Turn chicken and bake 25 minutes.

title: lentils - monastery style
directions: In a large pot, saute 3 to 5 minutes onions and carrot in olive oil. Add thyme and marjoram and saute one minute more. Add next five ingredients and cook, covered, for an hour or so until lentils are tender. Add sherry.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add balance of ingredients and mix.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until firm and golden brown.
Serves 6.
(Nice for brunch or lunch with a salad.)

title: war cake (ww 1)
directions: Bake in a greased tube pan about 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: aunt kath's salmon loaf
directions: In bowl mix salmon and juice.
Beat in cornflake crumbs, evaporated milk, butter, egg, lemon juice and poultry seasoning. Put mixture in loaf pan.
Set loaf pan in shallow pan of water. Cook at 350° for nearly an hour.

title: grandma's boiled raisin cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add egg and
mix
well.
Add boiled raisins and water.
Sift together
dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Bake in a 9
x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Use a large casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Slowly pour cornmeal into boiling water, stirring all the time, until mixture is thick and smooth. Add salt and butter (cut into chunks) and stir until mixture is thick and smooth.

title: beef dip in pumpernickel
directions: Scoop out center of loaf to form shell.
Cut center into chunks for dipping.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup and water; stir until dissolved. Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Do not stir!
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add vanilla and maple extracts.
Stir only until mixed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hamburger and noodle casserole
directions: Chop onion.
Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain hamburger grease.
Cook noodles; add ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the cucumbers, onions and salt; bury in ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Bring the sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cook slowly, until mixture is scalding but not boiling.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Combine water and pectin.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add pectin mixture to fruit and stir 3 minutes.
Pour into jars or freezer containers, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Freeze.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Use 1/2 of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in a greased 13x9x2 dish.
Combine rice and water in a bowl.
In a separate bowl combine soups, soup mix and peas; stir into rice mixture.
Spread over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle with parsley. Bake 10 - 15 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Bring water, butter, cocoa, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla to a boil
Pour boiled mixture over sugar, flour and soda.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour in greased and floured shallow pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake first 20 minutes, covered; uncover the last 20 minutes.

title: club sandwich salad
directions: In a large glass salad or serving bowl, layer half the lettuce. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Layer eggs, chicken, green onions, tomatoes, bacon and remaining half of the lettuce.
Frost top with mayonnaise to cover completely.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sausage corn supreme
directions: Mix sausage, corn, tomatoes, crumbs, onions and pepper.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and eggs.
Add sugars and cream again.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: smoky cheese ball
directions: Combine all but almonds.
Beat until fluffy.
Chill slightly. Shape into ball and coat with almonds.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal-molasses-marmalade bread
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Pour yeast into 1/3 cup hot water (105° to 115°).
Let sit for a few minutes.
Add butter and salt to oatmeal mixture.
Add molasses and orange marmalade.
Stir yeast and add.
Mix in 4 cups flour, one at a time.
Knead in the last 2 cups.
Place in bowl and let rise in a warm spot until doubled.
Cut down and place in 2 greased loaf pans and let rise until 1-inch above pans.
Bake on lowest rack of oven at 325° for 50 minutes.
Immediately remove from pans, place on rack and butter crust.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Put crushed crackers you saved, to go on top along with some cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: geneva stewart's company squash
directions: Combine all ingredients; add hot milk last.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage and onion.
Drain good; mix soup and milk.
Add rest of ingredients, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and put in a 3-quart Pyrex 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish. Cover and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch greased pan with half of the bread.
Place ham, broccoli, green pepper, onion and cheese over bread.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add 1 teaspoon dry mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Place remaining bread on top and pour liquid over all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out in morning.
Mix cornflakes and butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato slices and American cheese.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spread mixture on bread. Broil 5 inches from heat for 12 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese slices.
Broil again until cheese melts.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
Flake salmon and combine liquid and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a greased baking pan.
Or place in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar over grated cabbage and onion.
Mix good and set aside.
Mix salt, vinegar, celery seed and sugar with oil. Bring to a boil.
Pour boiling mix over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate 12 hours.
Keeps two weeks.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: ham grab bags
directions: Preheat
oven to 400°.	Drain sweet potatoes, reserving 1 tablespoon	syrup;	slice
sweet
potatoes.
On 4 sheets of heavy foil,
layer
the ham slices, sweet potatoes, beans and apples. Combine
cranberry sauce, reserved syrup and mustard. Spoon cranberry mixture over ham and vegetables.	If desired, sprinkle apple
slices
and	sweet potatoes with brown sugar. Wrap up foil pouches loosely.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400°
until heated
through,
about
20 minutes.
Transfer to serving plates, pouring juices over all.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade beef soup
directions: Cover beef with
water;
add
salt
and slice of onion. Cook under pressure slowly 1 hour.
Debone and chip lean meat. Skim off fat and
add
other
ingredients.
Bring
to boil and cook slowly about
minutes,
until
celery and carrots are done.
(If soup is
too watery, add another can of potato soup to thicken.)

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix meat, rice and seasonings and form into 10 or 12 small balls. Brown lightly in small amount of fat.
Drain off excess fat and add tomato sauce mixed with water.
Cover tightly and simmer 45 to 50 minutes.

title: uncle jimmy's "better than fruitcake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Hand mix (dough is very stiff, even up in pan).
Mix sugar, oil and beaten eggs.
Add soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Alternate parts of flour, apples, raisins and nuts. Grease and flour pan (13 x 9-inch tube or Bundt) and bake until done.
Top with confectioners sugar, butter frosting, Cool Whip or any topping you like.

title: deer baloney
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and mold into logs or sticks.
Place on cookie sheets or cake pans.
Cook 4 hours at 225°.
Cool completely before slicing or wrapping for freezer.

title: chocolate-covered frozen bananas
directions: You will need 6 to 10 wooden sticks.

title: hermits cookies
directions: Grease baking sheet lightly.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking.
Set to moderately hot temperature (400°).
Plump raisins. Cool.
Chop nuts.
Cream butter until shiny.
Add sugar in 2 portions, mixing until smooth after each.
Stir in raisins and nuts well.
Drop with a teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: whipped buttery spread(lo-cal)
directions: Place unwrapped margarine sticks in large mixing bowl; soften at room temperature until very soft.
Whip with mixer (not blender) on high speed until it loses the yellow color and turns white.
Add buttermilk, about 1/8 cup at a time, beating on low speed to mix, then whipping on high with each addition.
Add oil, if needed, to make it fluffier.
This takes about 10 minutes of beating to be fluffy.
Not to be used for frying.

title: potato cakes
directions: Peel potatoes and finely grate into large bowl.
Grate onion into same bowl.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Heat about 1/4-inch oil in heavy skillet.
Drop potato mixture by tablespoons into hot oil.
Brown until edges are crisp.
Turn and brown other side.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello (3 cups hot water and 3 cups cold water).
Slice bananas and add to jello.
Drain and add pineapple.
Save the juice.
Add marshmallows.
Stir and refrigerate until set.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook onions and potatoes in a pan with 2 cups of water until almost cooked.
Add fish and complete cooking.
When fish flakes easily, add butter, salt, pepper, savory and all milks.
Heat completely without boiling.
Sprinkle with paprika (optional) and let set for 15 minutes.

title: peach-lime jam (freezer)
directions: 1. Instead of a floral centerpiece for your dinner table, use your household plants.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Boil together sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let marinate in refrigerator several hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix well.
Cook over medium high-heat until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Time for 5 minutes.
Take from stove and add vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Put in a buttered 8 x 10-inch dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bernie's munching peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in a 1 and 1/2 quart microwave container.
Microwave on high power (10) for 3.10 minutes.
Add dry roasted peanuts and return to microwave for another 3.10 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla and microwave for 55 seconds.
Add baking soda and stir vigorously for 30 seconds until foamy. Quickly pour mixture onto a non-stick cookie sheet or lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet on a rack so air can circulate under it.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Loosen edges of peanut brittle with a table knife.
Gently turn over.
Tap gently with handle end of knife and break into pieces.
Total prep time, 10 minutes.
Yield:
1 lb. of delicious peanut brittle.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Cook vinegar, sugar, and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients half at a time to oil-sugar mixture.
Add eggs, alternating with dry ingredients; mix well.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan, lightly oiled.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk, mustard and pepper to boiling.
Add vegetables.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in ham, half of the cheese and macaroni.
Pour in casserole dish, which has been buttered.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, together.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Pour small amount in Bundt pan and freeze to make ice ring for punch.
Mix the remaining ingredients with Kool-Aid.

title: "kiss" cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter, egg, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Gradually add flour.
Roll by hand into 1-inch dough balls.
Roll in sugar that was set aside.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, on cookie sheets sprayed with non-stick spray. Place unwrapped kisses onto warm, out of the oven, cookies.
Cool.

title: pasta and shrimp
directions: In saucepan, blend butter (1/2) with heavy cream, pepper and cheese.
Apart, in skillet, melt garlic in butter until brown. Add shrimp and stir-fry.
Add parsley, basil and lemon on low heat.
Remove from heat.
Apart, prepare pasta.
Drain.
Pour cream sauce on pasta.
Garnish with shrimp.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler.
Stir constantly until desired thickness.
Keep in refrigerator and heat when used.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well. Squeeze out all the juice.
Break artichokes into small pieces and add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well. Add garlic powder and salt, mix.
Place in shallow casserole/baking dish that you will serve from.
Bake in 350 degree oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Remove from oven and blot excessive oil with paper towel. Serve immediately with Fritos (best large) or toast rounds.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In medium bowl, combine oats, flour, whole-wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in raisins and apples.
In large bowl combine egg, honey, oil, and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth batter.
Drop batter on ungreased baking sheet.
Use tsp. to drop dough 2 inches apart.
Press dough down to about 1 1/2 inch.
Bake 10-12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove cookies from baking pan to cooling rack.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into a roll and place in refrigerator.
When well chilled, slice and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
(May drop on cookie sheet and bake immediately after mixing.)

title: american goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients together with the beef and place in a casserole dish.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir once or twice.
Add water, if necessary.

title: orange juice cookies
directions: Sift, then measure flour.
Sift three times with soda and salt.
Cream butter until light and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition.
Slowly add eggs, which have been beaten until they are almost as stiff as whipped cream. Alternately add dry ingredients and liquid, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with additional coconut, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and cucumbers.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries with the marshmallows.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot water; let cool.
Add celery, salt, nuts, apples, sugar, pineapple, orange and ground peeling to cranberries and marshmallows mixture.
When Jell-O is cool, add to other ingredients and place in refrigerator until set.

title: pig tails or neck bones
directions: Wash the pig tails or neck bones and trim off the fat.
Place them in a pot and cover with water.
Add the seasonings.
Let come to a boil.
Turn the heat to low and cook slowly until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: raw radish dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend together cheese, lemon, dill seed, salt and garlic.
Add radishes and stir until blended.
Makes about 2 cups of dip.
Cover and refrigerate. This is delicious served with corn chips and crackers.
Make up to 4 hours ahead.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks.
Drain cherries and chop.
Chop pecans. Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup whipping cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit and pecans.
Combine 2 cups whipping cream and sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: honey apple ribs
directions: In a medium saucepan combine barbecue sauce, honey, jelly, catsup, 1/4 cup water, celery, brown sugar, relish, mustard and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Cool.

title: whirlagig cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Roll dough on cloth covered board dusted with flour.
Knead gently by folding, pressing and turning. Repeat 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough into 12 x 7-inch rectangle. Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough into long roll.
Pinch edges.
Cut into 1-inch slices. Place each slice into greased muffin cups (12 muffin cups).
Bake about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole dish mix soup, milk, soy, pepper, beans and 2/3 cups onions.
Stir. Sprinkle remaining onions over bean mixture.
Bake 5 minutes. or until onions are golden brown.

title: apple raisin sauce
directions: In medium size heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cloves.
Mix well. Add the apple juice, vinegar, lemon slices and raisins.
Cook over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.
Add butter or margarine.
Serve warm. Good with baked ham.

title: turkey dressing - southern
directions: Saute 3 cups chopped onions and 3 cups chopped celery; set aside.
Boil giblets from turkey in 1 1/2 quarts water with 1 onion and 1 cup celery.
Crumble breads and use enough of stock to soften.
Add onion and celery (2 cups each) and dry ingredients to crumble.
Beat 2 eggs and add.
Add 2 boiled eggs if desired.
Put in a bit more broth, place in pans sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° until top is crunchy.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat thoroughly (about 2 minutes).
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth. Cover with damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises.

title: persian yogurt soup(ash-e mast)
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rice and dill weed or spinach.
Boil over medium heat until rice is almost cooked.
Remove from heat and let stand until cool (approximately 1 hour).
Slowly stir in yogurt.
Add salt.
Simmer over low flame (10 to 15 minutes) until hot.

title: tomato salad
directions: In a large bowl, lay wedges of tomatoes. Drain olives. Add to tomatoes.
Slice peppers in strips and add to bowl. Add sliced onions into rings. Cube the cheese and add to bowl.
Pour dressing over all.
Toss and marinate until cold.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into mixing bowl; cut in shortening.
Add egg, bananas, rolled oats and nuts.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 1 1/2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie pans.
Bake at 375° about 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan immediately to cool on wire rack.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: smoked turkey, wild rice and mushroom muffins
directions: To make wild rice (1 cup):
Simmer 1/4 cup wild rice in 1 cup water in a small covered saucepan for 40 minutes or until rice bursts open and is tender.
Cool before using.

title: rice cooker jambalaya
directions: Stir all ingredients together in rice cooker.
Turn rice cooker on. After the bell rings signifying the rice is cooked, let jambalaya stand for 5 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 people. Preparation time: 10 to 15 minutes. Cooking time: 40 minutes.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Put sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Stir and add oil, salt and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add 1/2 cup beet juice.
Cut beets into bite size pieces and add to mixture.
Cook until it thickens.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in hot water. Add cold water, pineapple and bananas.
Pour in dish and cover with marshmallows; let stand overnight.
The next morning, take the sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Pour over first mixture. Whip the Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Pour over other mixture, then put coconut on top of this.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding and divide evenly on top of the 2 pies.

title: all purpose barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 2 cups of sauce.
Good on spareribs, chicken, pork chops and roast beef.

title: easy overnight sweet rolls
directions: Spread nuts in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange frozen rolls over nuts.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, then dry pudding mix, evenly distributing over rolls.
Place butter pieces over all on top.
Cover and let set overnight.
Rolls will thaw and rise.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until rolls are baked.
Turn immediately onto a serving dish.
Serve warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Add melted butter, eggs and pecans.
This will make 2 small pies.
Cook in 350° oven for 15 minutes, then in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend with wet mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place sugar sides up 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle each with 2 or 3 drops of water.
Bake 10 minutes in ???° oven.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Add margarine.
Cool. Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Add nuts. Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in rectangles. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 12 servings.

title: yum yum torte
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Chip up bacon, put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread rice in dish; add water. Place chicken on top of rice.
Add chopped celery.
Pour soup over all.
Bake at 325°
about 2 hours.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Press into a pie pan.
Spread with tomato paste.
Top with mushrooms.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, oregano flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.
If doubled, use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: delicious chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl until well blended.
Add egg and mix.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes, then remove.
Place on foil to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chef haller's white house dressing
directions: In a blender, place all ingredients except oil and blend at high speed 10 seconds. With blender running at low speed, gradually add the oil. Cover the blender and blend at high speed 10 seconds.
(You can also make the dressing by hand in a mixing bowl using a wire whisk.)
Store dressing in refrigerator, but serve it at room temperature.
Shake well before using.
Serve on garden or mixed green salads.

title: italian easter pie
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with pastry blender.
Scramble eggs with 1/4 cup milk (4 tablespoons).
Sprinkle over ingredients and toss with fork.
Add remainder of milk, 1 tablespoon at a time while mixing with fork.
When it is moist enough to form dough, shape it into 4 balls of dough and then roll out into pastry.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese and mayo together in low dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and add melted margarine over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: family chicken parmesan
directions: Place raw chicken in 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Cover with vegetables.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add alternately and beat well the flour and whipping cream.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and put into cold oven.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: snow ball cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until lemon colored, then add nuts and flour.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Put them on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for about 25 minutes.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar.
Put in airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: texas barbecue style
directions: Put brisket in shallow heavy pan with cover.
Pour all the remaining ingredients over meat.
Cover; bake at 325° for about 4 hours, or until tender.
Baste once in a while.
Remove cover; bake another 60 minutes, basting to glaze meat.
Skim off excess fat and thicken; serve as a sauce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Total baking time is 5 hours.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Blend boiling water into it gradually; then return to heat and cool slowly, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil and thicken.
Cook a few minutes, stirring constantly.
(Can be cooked in the microwave.) Set aside to cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix soup.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add tuna, then noodles.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered dish; top with bread crumbs or bran flakes.

title: chunky chili
directions: Brown turkey and add chopped vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6. Serve with dinner salad.

title: irish scones
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet with butter.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add water and mix.
Drop 1 spoonful of mixture onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 scones.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend until smooth.
(Roll in nuts; optional)
Makes 2 to 5 balls.
Chill before serving.
May freeze.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Heat through.
Add pepper and sour cream.
Heat.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: baklava
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cut phyllo in half crosswise and cut each half to fit pan.
Discard trimmings. Cover phyllo with a slightly damp towel.
Layer 10 sheets of phyllo in pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Combine coconut, Macadamia nuts, pecans, brown sugar and allspice.
Stir well.
Sprinkle 1/3 of nut mixture over phyllo, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Repeat procedure twice with remaining nut mixture, phyllo and butter, ending with butter phyllo.
Cut into diamond shapes using a sharp knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is browned.
Let cool completely.

title: boiled spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: In a pot place
the water;
bring to a boil and add the ribs. Cook until
tender.
In
a separate pot, put the sauerkraut.
Add the chopped
onion and the 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes
or
until
kraut
is very hot, stirring occasionally. Serve with the ribs.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, broth, sugar and 1 cup water. Stir thoroughly.
Set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon Crisco in large skillet or wok over high heat.
Add 1 minced garlic clove, broccoli, onions, celery and 1/4 cup water.
Stir.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Pour into large serving dish. Cover.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Melt remaining Crisco in skillet over high heat.
Add 1 minced clove of garlic and ginger. Stir in chicken.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add vegetables.
Stir soy sauce mixture and pour into skillet.
Stir until vegetables and chicken are coated and sauce is clear.
Turn off heat.
Serve over cooked rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 people.

title: easy cassoulet(6 servings)
directions: In skillet, cook sausage, onion and garlic until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Add ham, parsley and bay leaf; mix well.
Stir in undrained beans, wine and cloves.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 40 to 45 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve in bowls with hot corn bread.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Coat chicken in margarine and crushed crackers.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour uncover to brown.
(Pork chops can also be fixed this way.)

title: italian sweet slaw
directions: Layer shredded cabbage in a bowl alternately with onion rings. Top with 7/8 cup sugar.
In a pan, bring vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onion in a bowl while hot.
Cover and let set in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese in a large bowl.
Add flour and sausage.
Mix with hands until dough is stiff.
Form into a small ball and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Turn occasionally. Cook 8 to 12 minutes on each side.
Yields 80 balls.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add
pumpkin,
eggs
and
dry ingredients. Drop by large tablespoonfuls
onto greased cookie sheets.
Baking time: 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese-spinach cups
directions: Drain cottage cheese well using a strainer. Set aside.
Drain chopped spinach well and press between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine cottage cheese, spinach and next 4 ingredients; stir well. Spoon 2 teaspoons mixture into each pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: special k d'lites
directions: Measure syrup and sugar into large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter and nuts. Add cereal and mix well.
You can drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper and shape into clusters or press mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: irene's "greco"
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in a small amount of oil.
Add meat and brown until done.
Add mushrooms, tomato sauce and corn; mix completely.
Add to macaroni.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Prepare pudding, using mixing instructions on box.
Add cooked rice and cinnamon; mix well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt cream cheese in ketchup over low heat.
Dissolve gelatin separately in warm water.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, lemon juice, dry mustard and shrimp; blend thoroughly.
Fold in mayonnaise.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave out cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until soft.
Mix in bowl with all other ingredients. Roll into ball and chill in refrigerator around 2 hours.
Serve plain or roll in chopped pecans.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Fill jars with apples, then cook remaining ingredients until thick.
Pour over apples in jars. Cook in pressure cooker for 8 minutes on 5 pounds or put in water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Measure into mixing bowl (all measurements level).
Mix first 7 ingredients.
Now, add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Pour into baking pans and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: flank steak florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180° C).
Pound the steak on both sides with a mallet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together broccoli, rice, mushroom soup and cheese; put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour butter on top and sprinkle chopped onion on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Stir until smooth and mixed well. Do not beat. Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Beat well. In separate bowl, combine all dry ingredients, including cereal. Make a well in the dry ingredients; pour buttermilk mixture into well.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Batter can be refrigerated for up to 4 weeks.

title: german pancakes
directions: Put a 10-inch iron skillet in the oven.
Preheat oven to 425°. Beat 2 eggs lightly.
Add milk, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Mix until blended.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in the skillet.
Pour in batter.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with melted butter and powdered sugar.
Makes one pancake.

title: pepper hash
directions: Put all 3 vegetables through grinder.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook for 1 hour after it starts to boil.
Yields approximately 6 pints.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and ham in margarine.
Add broccoli, salt, pepper, basil and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and add milk.
Simmer 30 minutes, then add cornstarch, stirring well.
Add cheese; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: low-fat burgers
directions: Mix ingredients well; form into 6 or 8 patties.
Spray frypan with nonstick spray.
Cook over medium heat, or put on grill. Serve in hamburger buns with lettuce, tomato, pickles and chips.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add garlic; cook 15 minutes longer, then add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat for 1 hour. Salt to taste.
Plus other Polish secret ingredients.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs, flour, milk, spices, jam, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350 degrees. Frost with caramel icing.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in soda, salt and flour.
Add milk.
(Feel free to add chocolate chips or M&M's here.)
Make into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Cook rice in oil until color changes slightly.
Do not brown. Add onions and peppers.
Add cheese, stock, salt and pepper.
Stir to mix.
Top with oleo or butter.
Cover tightly and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix well and chill dough about 1 hour in refrigerator.
Roll chilled dough out in balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: homemade paint
directions: Mix water and dishwashing liquid.
Add food coloring to make vivid colored paint.
Make sure your future Rembrandt wears an apron or play clothes to do this project.

title: carol's layered taco salad with meat
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, layer in the following order: lettuce, chopped onion, drained chopped tomatoes and chopped black olives.
Prepare meat mixture.
Fry ground beef; drain.
Add water and taco seasoning.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool.
This is the next layer after black olives.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.

title: italian coconut cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks and margarine.
Add flour, baking soda, buttermilk, coconut, walnuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and add to batter last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top of cake is browned.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add soups, tomatoes, broth, garlic and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
Tear tortillas in strips.
Alternate layers of tortillas, chicken and cheese in a casserole pan, putting a layer of sauce first.
Pour remaining sauce over layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: Drain the mandarin oranges, pineapple and peaches, then mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together then chill.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake the pie crust for 5 to 7 minutes or until very light golden.
Remove from the oven and let cool. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Meanwhile, cut candy bars in half lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Place the candy bar pieces over the bottom of the partially baked crust.

In a small bowl, combine the sugar and cream cheese; beat until smooth. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the sour cream and peanut butter, beating until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture over the candy bar pieces.

title: pork chops surprise
directions: Place chops in casserole or baking dish.
Place slice of lemon on each.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Spoon catsup on each chop.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes to brown chops.
Add 1/2 cup water for gravy, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding as directed on the box.
After pudding is cooked, remove from heat and add cake mix; stir only until moistened.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean mushrooms; remove caps and chop stems.
Mix cracker crumbs with salt, pepper, parsley, onions and melted butter.
Add chopped stems.

title: sugar-free chocolate cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, cocoa, sugar replacement, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and beat to mix.
Pour into 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring margarine, Coke and cocoa to a boil; add to sugar and vanilla.
Mix together and spread over hot cake.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread; spread with butter.
Mix all ingredients but 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Put toast in a buttered dish. Pour milk mixture over toast; let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pie over pastry puffs
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, not browned.
Blend in flour and broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cubed chicken or turkey and mixed vegetables.
Heat until bubbly again.
Pour over individual Pastry Puffs.

title: potato latkes(hanukkah)
directions: Grate potatoes in food processor.
Turn into sieve and drain. Put onion, eggs and salt in food processor.
Blend.
Add potatoes. Blend.
Fry on oil in pan.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm. Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued cornish hens
directions: Remove giblets and neck from hens (save for other use).
Cut each hen in half with shears or a boning knife.
Rub skin with oil.
Place hens on barbecue grill over medium-hot coals, cooking for 25 to 35 minutes, turning frequently.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix
all
together
and put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika
on top along with sliced almonds.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve on crackers.

title: peachy chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except peaches.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Add peaches and heat.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and powder.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Add butter, eggs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper to mashed carrots and mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: new york cheese cake(from a real new yorker.)
directions: You will need a spring-form pan.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make one cup.
Add gleatin; chill until partially set.
Measure 1 1/2 cups; pour into a 6 cup mold. Chill until set, but not firm.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Blend into remaining jello.
Add pear, pineapple, almonds and cherries.
Spoon into mold.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: In medium bowl, mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine until blended, kneading with hands, if necessary.
Shape peanut butter mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
When peanut butter balls are firm, in saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate chips and shortening until melted and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients in a large bowl (because of 7-Up fizz). When jello starts to thicken, add pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and bananas.

title: quiche - impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli, slightly undercooked.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and green pepper in a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (1 minute on high). Pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until clean knife comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix until well blended.
Serve with chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Add dry ingredients to oil mixture and mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch pans for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: linguica jag(a cape verdean rice)
directions: Strain water from beans and corn.
Cut the meat into quarter size pieces and then in 1/2.
Pour enough oil in a large saucepan. Add onions and linguica.
Saute until onions are soft.
Add water, rice, enough paprika to turn water red, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir well.
Add strained lima beans or corn.
Stir for the last time.
Add bay leaves.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Check in 20 minutes.
Use a fork to gently move rice to see if all water is absorbed.
It's best when rice just starts to stick to the bottom of the pan but not burning.
The rice should be dry.
Remove bay leaves and serve.
Good as a side dish with meat or poultry.

title: california chicken(or pork chops)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion soup over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle rice over soup.
Lay chicken pieces on rice.
Dot with butter.
Pour over this the mushroom soup and water that has been mixed together.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wesleyan peach pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place 6 peeled peach halves, cut side down in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: popovers (low calorie)
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fill tins slightly less than 1/2 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° to 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not open oven door. Makes 6.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon sugar in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour filling over sugar and flour.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks.
Cut fruit in chunks and roll in 1/2 cup of flour.
Add the flour to sugar and egg yolks and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Beat egg whites stiff and add to mix last.
Bake in 275° oven for about 3 hours.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time (mixing well after each).
Fold in bananas and chopped nuts. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough; allow to rose (covered).
Divide dough in half.
Turn out on a floured surface.
Roll dough to 12-inch rectangle.
Combine egg and Parmesan cheese.
Spread half of mixture on dough.
Layer half pepperoni and half Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 teaspoon oregano.
Roll dough jelly roll fashion.
Repeat with the rest of dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish and bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash small cucumbers and pack into pint or quart jars.
Add ingredients.
Be sure to sterilize jars and tops.
Will be ready in a couple of weeks.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion until translucent, then add garlic.
Add flour slowly.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Add broth slowly and stir until smooth.
Add milk and cheese; stir.
Add broccoli.
Thin with milk if needed.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven at 350°.
Pour potatoes into butter and stir.
Mix remaining ingredients (not butter and corn flake crumbs).
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Top with 1/2 stick melted butter and corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "chicken salad"
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Serve with crackers or fill fresh tomatoes.
So good.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together. Reserve enough cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: everyday casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, add salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 meat in baking dish, then 1/2 macaroni in layers. Then a layer of Velveeta.
Repeat in same order.
Pour tomato sauce over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: arizona pecan pie
directions: Beat together first 7 ingredients; stir in nuts and orange peel.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° until set.

title: chicken breast diane(microwave)
directions: Pound chicken between waxed paper.
Salt and pepper.
In microwave dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken in dish, coating breasts on both sides.
Microwave on High 3 minutes. Let rest 1 minute; turn breast over.
Microwave again on High 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: classic oven baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Cook bacon crisp, drain and crumble. In a 1 quart casserole combine beans, onion, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar, mustard, and Worcestershire sauce. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every 15 minutes

title: oven chicken
directions: Spread soup, sour cream and water mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the brown sugar, butter, water and salt in a heavy skillet.
Cook until mixture boils.
Add the potatoes or yams and cook slowly, turning occasionally, about 20 minutes or until potatoes have a caramel-like glaze.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry-walnut bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans; sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts in the bottom of each pan.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cardamom, salt and nutmeg. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened; stir in remaining nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.
Makes 2.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownies according to package directions.
When cool, crumble them.
Prepare chocolate mousse filling mix according to box and refrigerate for about 30 minutes or until spreadable. Spread half the crumbled brownies into a large glass bowl.
Place half the chocolate mousse on top of the brownies, then half the brickle and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers.
Garnish with chocolate bar either broken into small pieces or by making curls.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender, drain and rinse.
Saute onion in butter, add the seasonings and reserved liquid.
Blend in soup, stir until smooth.
Add milk gradually stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Mix the spaghetti, mushrooms, pimento, and cooked chicken in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over top and mix well.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook the spinach according to package directions; drain and squeeze out remaining moisture.
Add all remaining ingredients to spinach.
Cover and refrigerate mixture for at least 4 hours. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet for about 20 minutes at 325°.
Spinach Balls can be frozen and used as needed.
Serve as appetizer or with meal.

title: skillet beef and potatoes
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain.
Cook onions, green pepper, garlic and carrots until tender.
Stir in potatoes and beef.
Add tomatoes (chopped), liquid and seasonings.
Bring to boil, then simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: chile verde
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Heat oil in deep skillet and brown meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered 1 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove lid.
Simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes or to desired consistency.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add strawberry flavored gelatin and beat until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and hot water and boil to 252° by candy thermometer.
Add syrup very slowly to egg whites, beating continuously (be sure syrup is kept hot at all times).
Continue beating by hand with a large spoon until candy becomes dull.
Add nuts and drop on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken with beef
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 1 piece of bacon, uncooked. Place dried beef on bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Place chicken on top. Mix soup with sour cream; spread on top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Do not cover unless getting to brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cream of mushroom, mayonnaise, egg, and cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into 9 x 12 casserole dish.
Crush crackers and top casserole.
Pour melted margarine on top and cover.
Cook at 325 degrees for about 40 minutes and remove lid. Cook until topping is golden brown.

title: american beef and peppers
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet; add soup, water and seasonings. Simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add pepper and onion rings to meat; continue cooking until tender.
Serve over rice.
(Additional water may be added, if needed, to keep the consistency of rich gravy.)

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add syrup and sugar. Bring to a slow simmer. Add peanuts. After done, add the soda.
Pour on cookie sheet. Do not spread.

title: no-guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate on low.
Cool slightly. Put in food processor all except chocolate and the powdered sugar. Beat until smooth. Add melted chocolate and beat well.
Pour into lightly buttered pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: orange biscuits
directions: In a saucepan, combine orange juice, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and orange peel.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes. Divide among 12 muffin cups; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With a fork, stir in milk until mixture forms a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, knead the dough 1 minute.
Roll into a 9-inch square, about 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine the cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Roll up.
Cut into 12 slices, about 3/4 inch thick.
Place slices, cut side down, over orange mixture in muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 16 minutes.
Cool for 2 to 3 minutes; remove from pan.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Cut unpeeled apple rings in skillet.
Bring honey, cinnamon, vinegar and salt to boiling.
Add apples.
Cook, stirring often, until translucent, for 10 to 20 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Put all ingredients in fondue and simmer 1 hour.
If too dry, add more bourbon.
Can use cocktail hot dogs or cut regular wieners into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Serve with toothpicks.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Dad will just love these!

title: mole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender, adding salt to taste. Remove from heat; let cool.
Shred the meat from the bones.
Put broth in a pan and add the mole and garlic.
Make sure it is not too thick, if it is keep adding chicken broth, then add the chicken and let it cook with mole for 10 to 15 minutes over low heat.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drain pineapple.
Chill for 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand 20 minutes. Add oleo and remaining ingredients.
Mix well in a large bowl. Add 1 cup nuts and coconut (optional).
Pour in greased and floured sheet pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: hidden valley ranch sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease a muffin tin and press one wrapper in each cup. Brush with oil.
Bake for 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins.
Place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.

title: beef and noodle medley
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add meat and saute for 5 minutes.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; saute 5 minutes longer.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until noodles are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: low calorie cheese and herb dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and stir until smooth and creamy or process in blender.
Allow to stand in refrigerator a few hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Makes 1 cup.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, poppy seed and oil.
Add water and beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then beat for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: venison steak
directions: Mix beaten eggs with milk and salt and pepper.
Soak for 5 to 10 minutes.
Then roll in flour and fry until brown.

title: vermont cooler float
directions: Combine milk, vanilla ice cream and syrup in blender.
Spoon ice cream into glass and pour mixture on top.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water, diced bananas, drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator until congealed.
Cook sugar, flour, egg and 1 cup pineapple juice until thick.
Allow to cool. When cool, spread over congealed Jell-O mixture.
Whip the whipping cream.
Blend with cream cheese; beat until light and fluffy.
Spread over second layer.
Sprinkle sharp cheese over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: raisin nut nuggets
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and add eggs and water.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Freeze in plastic bags.
Take out about 30 minutes to thaw.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Stir dry ingredients until mixed thoroughly.
Add milk, stir again and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed.
Serve over ice cream.
Store in container in refrigerator. Will keep for weeks!

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water; drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix and whip until fluffy.
Put in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick au gratin potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in a bowl.
Add the flour, mustard, cheese and seasonings.
Mix gently.
Spread in greased casserole dish; spread enough milk over it to barely cover.
Cook in center of oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until just brown.
Serves 4.

title: egg foo young
directions: Combine vegetables, pork and seasoning.
Add eggs.
Toss until egg covers.
Spoon mixture on lightly greased skillet.
Flatten like pancake.
Cover over light heat.
Turn.
Garnish with green onion.

title: black jack barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer 25 minutes. Strain or puree in blender.
Refrigerate.
Makes 5 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper, and 1/2 can onion rings. Bake uncovered in a greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake for 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
(I use Durkee's Fried Onion Rings.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Add spinach, tomatoes, olives and scallions.
Fold in dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Set
cup cereal aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spread
into
greased
x 7-inch baking dish.
Crush reserved cereal and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool a few minutes and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and stir until smooth.
Then add pumpkin, milk and egg.
Pour mixture into 9-inch unbaked pastry crust.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: weight watchers banana cream pie
directions: In a microwave bowl, heat peanut butter and honey on High for 20 to 50 seconds (until soft).
Mix well and stir in cereal. Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill. Prepare pudding with skim milk or 1%.
Slice bananas over bottom crust.
Spread pudding on top.
Chill.

title: small cheesecakes
directions: Combine
cream	cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs in	mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Line small tart
pans with small paper cups.
Place 1 vanilla wafer upside down
in
paper
cup.
Place
tablespoon
of cheese filling in each
cup.	Bake
at
350°	for
18 to 20 minutes. Crack will appear
on top and they will appear like they have fallen.	Let cool.
When
cooled, place 1 teaspoon cherry pie filling on top. Makes 50.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13 baking dish with 1/3 of graham crackers.
Mix together pudding and milk until thickened.
Fold in cool whip and mix well.
Spread half of pudding mixture on top of graham crackers.
Put another layer (1/3)
of graham crackers and remaining half of pudding.
Top with last third of graham crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Then frost with chocolate icing, sealing edges.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and mix until blended. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add this alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries. Grease muffin tins well (tops also). Fill cups and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: spaghetti squash with herbed garlic sauce
directions: Prick the squash with a fork 2 to 3 times to prevent bursting. Place in a pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour until the squash depresses easily when pressed with fingers. Remove from oven and halve at once or squash will continue cooking. Let cool briefly, then scoop out seeds.
With a fork, pull out strands, leaving only a shell.
There should be approximately 4 cups.
Heat butter in a small pan over low heat; add flour and garlic; stir over lowest heat for 3 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Scoop out pulp from potatoes into a large mixing bowl.
(I use cut up skins, if desired).
Add celery seed, cream, milk and one cup of water.
Mix until thick like gravy.
In a large Dutch oven, put butter or margarine.
Saute chopped onion until clear. Add potato
mixture, salt and pepper to onion.
Heat; garnish with shredded cheese, bacon bits and onions.
Soup should be thick.

title: *lenten cake with nuts and raisins
directions: Sift together flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts. Beat oil, sugar, orange juice and zest. Add dry ingredients, stirring just enough to combine thoroughly.
Pour mixture into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine in a small bowl the Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese. Combine in a large bowl the milk and pudding. Mix Eagle Brand milk into milk mixture and fold in a large carton Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers in a large Pyrex, then a layer of bananas, continuing to layer, making sure pudding is on top. Crumble a few wafers on top.

title: ham 'n broccoli bake
directions: Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and red pepper. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Arrange broccoli on bottom of a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Top with ham and cheese sauce. Cover. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls into very hot, deep pot of grease.
Hush puppies should turn over by themselves when brown on one side.
Remove when golden brown.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut up fryer and cover with water.
Add one can of Ro-Tel tomatoes with chilies, 2 onions (chopped), one chopped bell pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer one hour.
Remove chicken.
Add one can tomato sauce, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and parsley (optional).
Add one package of Old Smokehouse creole gumbo mix. Bring back to a boil.
Let boil 25 to 30 minutes slowly.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut in bite size pieces and add to gumbo.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 or 10 inch pie plate.
Mix together all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: individual baked alaska
directions: Slice a piece of angel cake and press it into a coffee cup. Sugar the berries (1 tablespoon) and slice if necessary.
Press them into the cake.
If using sorbet or ice cream, only fill the cup half way with the berries.
Add the scoop of ice cream and fill the cup with more berries.
Invert the cup.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, then add the 1/4 cup sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread the meringue on cakes and bake in a preheated 400° oven for approximately 3 to 4 minutes or until meringue is slightly golden.
Approximately 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Heat Wesson in heavy skillet.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt in paper bag.
Shake chicken in bag to coat evenly. Brown pieces in hot oil on all sides.
Pour off drippings. Arrange onion and green pepper on chicken.
Pour Hunt's tomato sauce over all.
Simmer, covered, 50 minutes, spooning sauce over chicken occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and let cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled gelatin and mix well. Fold in whipped Milnot.
Crush graham crackers and mix with butter.
Pack in well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: quick bar for the holiday
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to sugar mixture and mix well. Put half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Scoop ice cream into a ball, cover and freeze until firm. Combine graham cracker crumbs and cinnamon.
Roll ice cream in mixture and freeze.
Beat egg and milk until well blended.
Quickly coat ice cream in egg mixture, then crumbs again and return to freezer.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours.
Heat oil to 375° in deep fryer. Fry ice cream one at a time for 10 to 15 seconds.
Serve immediately with topping and honey.

title: white bread(three loaves)
directions: Mix and knead all ingredients.
Oil pans.
Put dough in pans and let raise until double.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes.
Glass pans or dishes take less time.
When they are finished, brush with butter.

title: hungry boys casserole
directions: Saute in a large skillet the first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4. Reserve 1 cup for biscuits.
Add pork and beans and lima beans.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla. Beat well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Just before brownies are done, melt chocolate chips (over low heat or in microwave) with sweetened condensed milk and remaining 1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Immediately spread over hot brownies.
Cool; chill.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: mom's mexican cornbread(good crowd pleaser)
directions: Brown the meats with the two yellow onions.
Layer 1/2 of the mix with the meats and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine creamed margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Dissolve baking powder in milk and add to mixture. Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: red beans and rice with turkey kielbasa
directions: Cook rice according to pkg. directions omitting any fat and set aside.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar until forms stiff peaks.
Spread over top of pie.
Brown in 450° oven.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Flatten 1 can rolls. Mix cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice and spread over flattened rolls. Top with other can rolls. Glaze with egg white. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty hodge podge stew
directions: Brown beef, onions and garlic slightly.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer in a large pot for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 12 to 14.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook the first 8 ingredients until mixture thickens.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites real stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar. Put on pie and brown.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat in sugar, water, flour, vanilla and salt until blended.
Stir in coconut and melted butter.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool to warm.

title: no crust shoo-fly cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie dough.
Mix water, molasses and baking soda in a large bowl.
Reserve 1 cup of the crumb mixture.
Mix rest of crumb mixture with the liquid mixture. Sprinkle the 1 cup of crumbs on the top.
Put into a greased oblong 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage skillet
directions: Cut sausage into chunks.
Combine with 3/4 cup converted rice, 1 can celery soup, 3/4 cup water and 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet on medium heat.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix in bowl pineapple and juice, pudding and drained fruit cocktail.
Add 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Keep chilled until serving.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour and other dry ingredients; add milk and egg yolk. Mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Add oil.
Heat waffle iron on both sides; grease well.
Put a little of batter in center; close iron.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup.

title: cold tomato-yogurt soup
directions: Bring medium pot of water to boil.
Add tomatoes; blanch 30 seconds.
Remove with slotted spoon to bowl of cold water.
Drain. Peel, core and chop tomatoes.
Transfer to blender.
Add yogurt, onion, sugar, chopped basil, salt and pepper; puree until smooth. Transfer to medium bowl.
Cover and chill up to 8 hours.
Serve garnish with sliced basil and chopped tomato.

title: snow drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar slowly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Place in oven.
Shut door and immediately turn off oven.
Don't open.
Leave overnight or for 6 hours.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: wonderful hand lotion or diaper cream
directions: Put some petroleum jelly in a dish and mix enough cornstarch with it to make a white cream or salve.
Works wonders on rough hands or diaper rash.
Store in covered container.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Use reserved juice.
Grease large cake pan, 9 x 13-inch, that has edges.
Pour cake batter into prepared pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Let cool.
Mix pudding mix with 1 cup milk.
Beat cream cheese into pudding mix. Fold by hand the Cool Whip into the mixture. Spread mixture onto cool cake. Sprinkle pineapple on top of pudding, then chopped cherries, nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Mix together dry ingredients, then add to shortening mixture.
Chill dough; shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Will be soft.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
In large bowl, mix eggs, milk, Mozzarella cheese (3 cups) and a shake of garlic powder.
Add spaghetti to this mixture and spread in greased pans, 2 (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Brown hamburger; add Prego.
Add oregano and basil.
Spread over spaghetti mixture. Can be frozen at this point before baking.
Place slices of pepperoni all over top and sprinkle the remaining 3 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off all visible fat from meat.
Cut flank steak lengthwise (with grain) into strips about 1/4-inch thick (or less).
Combine seasonings; sprinkle over cut up steak strips and mix well. Arrange strips of steak, flat and close together, on wire cooling racks set onto cookie sheets.
Bake in slow oven at 175° for 3 to 4 hours, or until dry (but not dried up and brittle; it should still be a bit chewy).
Cool on paper towels.
Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour and sugar once, then measure.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually until well creamed.

Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition. Add crushed bananas and lemon juice alternately with the dry ingredients, adding 1/3 of the flour, then half of the banana mixture, another third of the flour and the rest of the bananas. To the remaining flour, add the nuts and stir until all is blended.
Fill greased and floured pans (11 x 4 x 2-inch) 2/3's full and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tennessee pride country bread stuffing for turkey
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet, breaking up with a fork as it cooks, until all pink color is gone.
Pour off and discard all but 1/2 cup of accumulated liquid.
Add celery and onion to sausage in a skillet.
Cook onion in a large bowl.
Add sausage mixture, parsley and enough chicken broth to moisten.
Mix together gently. Will stuff one 12 to 14 pound turkey.
Bake excess in an ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon and noodle dish
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, mustard, paprika and salt.
Add milk and cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Add salmon, olives and mushrooms.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin into boiling water.
Add strawberries with juice, pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan half of mixture, let stand.
Spread sour cream over firm mixture and add the rest of gelatin mixture.

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, brown sugar and butter.
Spread half of it in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg yolks until thick. Gradually beat in sugar, then gently fold in egg whites, then whipped cream.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Pour over crumbs in pan. Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add pineapple juice and water, strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of the mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish as first layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread top evenly with the sour cream.
Gently spoon rest of strawberry mixture on top and refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown floured and seasoned pork chops in butter.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Cover with sliced onion.
Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick and place over onion.
Season with a little seasoning salt.
Mix mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over chops. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake a little longer if potatoes aren't quite tender.

title: tenderloin roast
directions: Marinate tenderloin in Wilson steak sauce and teriyaki sauce for 3 to 4 hours, then drain. Mix salt, pepper, mustard, ginger and paprika. Rub on top of tenderloin. Top with pineapple preserves. Wrap in foil or use browning bag. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: insulated pigs
directions: Peel each potato and make a lengthwise hole in it with an apple corer.
Boil potatoes in salted water for 5 minutes.
Boil sausage links in same water for 10 minutes, then insert a sausage in each potato.
Make a sauce of butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Roll potatoes in butter mixture, then corn flakes. Dust with paprika.
Put potatoes on rack in a pan; bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serve hot from oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together.
Enough for one 10-inch pie.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until table knife blade comes out clean, about 1 hour.
One large can equals 4 pieces.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and saute until crisp.
Add onion, celery, pepper, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire and liquid smoke.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add beans and heat well.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix
shortening, egg, brown sugar and vanilla together. Add sifted
flour
and	salt
to
creamed mixture.
Roll into balls. Dip
in
slightly
beaten
egg whites.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place
1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake	for
5 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven; place thumbprint in
center. Bake for 8 more minutes.
Cool.
Thumbprint may be filled with jam.

title: spinach calzone
directions: Step 1:
Take frozen bread out of freezer and let it rise (6 to 8 hours).

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well and store in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator.
Use as desired.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: hunters goulash
directions: Brown meat; remove from skillet and saute onions in same pan. In kettle, put tomatoes and celery.
Boil until celery is tender. Add to onions and meat and season well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender, then add 2 cups shell macaroni.
Stir well.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour, or until shells are done.
Add more liquid if needed.
Before serving, add lima beans; mix well 5 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: apple nobby cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Place shortening, eggs and sugar in a large bowl.
Cream until smooth with portable electric mixer.
Measure flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg into medium bowl.
Stir to combine.
Add flour mixture to shortening and beat until all ingredients are moistened.
With a wooden spoon, stir in vanilla and diced apples.
Press into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes; cool.

title: grammie's jelly roll
