directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 8-inch pie shell (uncooked).
Bake at 325° until done.
Top will be brown.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In large mixing bowl, combine beef, taco seasoning, cheese and water. Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into triangles. Arrange in a circle on baking stone with wide ends overlapping in center and points toward outside (there should be a 5 inch opening in center). Scoop meat mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle. Bring points of triangle up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of ring. (Filling will no be completely covered.) Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Cut off top of green bell pepper, clean and fill with salsa. Shred lettuce and chop tomato, onion and black olives around pepper. Garnish with sour cream, cut and serve.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat tomatoes, garlic salt and cumin until boiling.
Add cheese and cook over low heat until melted. Add can of chili and heat through. Serve with corn chips.

title: apple roll
directions: Combine both sugars, oleo and water.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place in oven and bring to a boil.

title: cheese balls
directions: Form dough from cheese, flour, margarine and salt.
Form small ball of dough around 1/2 of a date and 1/2 pecan.
Place on cookie sheet, pecan side down.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: zucchini
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter and saute onions until clear.
Add zucchini, tomatoes and the mushrooms.
Continue cooking, covered, for 5 minutes on low to medium heat.

title: chicken-waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves or croissants.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add beaten eggs.
Add bananas and flour mixture.
Mix well. Turn into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch loaves.

title: veal scallopini
directions: In large frying pan, brown veal in about a tablespoon of oil (olive preferred) with the onions.
In separate saucepan, put remaining ingredients.
When peppers soften, turn off.
When veal is cooked, pour sauce and peppers over veal and cook on low flame for about 1/2 hour.
Serve with white rice.

title: banana-nut salad
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
saucepan.
Slowly
bring to boil. Slice bananas in dish down the center, then in half.
Place in dish. Top with sauce.
Chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 250° for five hours.
Leave cover on pan while baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, celery, onions, green peppers and garlic in 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Season with pepper, salt and Accent. Cook slowly for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling water until almost done and add to meat mixture in large casserole dish. Cover with American cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done through and through.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, brown beef and onion.
Drain any fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into bowls and top with shredded cheese.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Cut up chipped beef and green peppers into small pieces.
Add all ingredients together except walnuts.
Mix and put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Cook at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with chips!

title: venison tenderloin
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter.
Saute steaks with sliced onion, sprinkling with Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap with bacon slices and serve with toothpicks.

title: punch
directions: *Note: You can use any flavor of Jell-O.
Depends on what color of punch you want.

title: betty best rolls
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm water and let sit until foamy (about 5 minutes).
It may help to add a teaspoon of honey or sugar, to feed the yeast.
Meanwhile, in food processor, place flour, salt, sugar and oil.
Process until mixed.
Add yeast water through tube while processing.
Mixture should roll into a ball and not stick to the bowl too much.
If it does, add a little flour, until it balls up.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and vanilla pudding.
Cook over medium heat; stir until it boils.
Remove and let it cool.
Combine fruits and mix in pudding.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill.
Makes 6 cups.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook potatoes until done with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and celery salt.
Add to potatoes and English peas.
Ready to serve.

title: pecan-cheese ball
directions: Cut cheeses and onion into chunks and grind in food grinder or process in food processor.
Sprinkle with salt and mix thoroughly. Chill.

title: bean tacos
directions: In bowl, mash beans.
Add onion, taco powder, cumin and garlic.
Fry in pan until tender.
Add beans and cook until thick. Makes enough for 6 tacos.

title: macaroni salmon squares
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter and stir in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk, cooking until thick.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to the slightly beaten eggs and return to hot mixture.
Add cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and salmon.
Turn into a greased 9-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan and bake a 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sheepherder's bread
directions: Heat water, sugar, margarine and salt until warm.
Pour mixture into large bowl; stir in yeast.
Cover; let stand about 15 minutes in a warm place, until mixture is bubbly.
Stir in 4 cups flour, beating to form a thick batter.
Stir in 3 more cups of flour to make a soft dough.
Knead enough remaining flour to a moderately stiff dough.
Shape into a ball.
Put into a greased bowl and grease top.
Cover and let raise until double.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in milk and shortening (melted).
Spread in 9-inch square pan and sprinkle with 1/4 cup cocoa and brown sugar. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350°, about 45 minutes.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water. Combine juices. Add to gelatin mix. Chill. Add ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into punch just before serving.
Yields 40 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Remove from heat.
In bowl, combine onion mixture, sour cream, 1/2 of cheese, milk, chilies and cumin.
Add drained hominy.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over top and serve.

title: country-style pork ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes, until sauce is reduced to about 4 cups. Makes 4 cups.

title: care a lot cloud cake
directions: Put pound cake on plate; cut it in half.
Pour half of orange juice on the bottom piece of cake.
Spread the jam on the bottom of the other half.
Put pieces together with jam in the middle. Pour rest of orange juice on cake; cover with whipped cream.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Grind garlic, basil and nuts together in a processor or with a pestle.
Add the cheese.
Then slowly add olive oil.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple fritters
directions: In a bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth. Pare, core and slice apples thinly.
Dip apple slices into the batter so each one is well-coated.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Use 2 or 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water, according to taste.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Melt margarine in boiler. Add sugar, dates, vanilla and eggs; mix in boiler and cook 10 minutes on low heat. Mix cereal and pecans in bowl. Let syrup cool and stir in cereal and pecans. Roll out into rolls; then roll in coconut.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Add mixed vegetables, then combine broth and cream of chicken.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Next combine milk, Bisquick and margarine.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is browned.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Mix apples and cranberries and cover with sugar.
Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Then add pineapple, pecans and the apple/cranberry mixture.
Chill.

title: no bake chocolate chewy cookies
directions: While you mix margarine, sugar, Vitamite and cocoa in a saucepan and bring it to a rolling boil, have the kids roll out the waxed paper.
After it boils, remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Let the kids take turns stirring until the peanut butter is well mixed, then have the kids drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Leave until completely cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pork pies
directions: Combine ingredients and press in tin; bake.

title: cream of coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together sour cream, cooking oil, eggs, cream of coconut and cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix in crockpot the soup and rice. Place chicken on top of mixture, then add celery. Cook for 3 hours on high or 4 hours on low.
To make 6 servings, add more 1/2 c. rice, and 2 breasts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt and put in refrigerator until remainder of cake is mixed. Sift sugar and cream it with butter until light and creamy.
Sift flour, then resift with baking powder, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients in 3 parts to the butter mixture alternately with thirds of the sour cream.
Beat batter until smooth after each addition.
Beat in flavoring.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: somersault cobbler
directions: Can use self-rising flour, but omit salt and baking powder.

title: savory cheese puffs
directions: Place crumbs in 2-quart casserole.
Add cheese and ham (if desired).
Sprinkle with flour and top with melted oleo.
Combine eggs, milk and vegetable packet.
Mix well and pour over all in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good as a side dish.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cook butter and sugar until boiling.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of mixture for garnish.
Press mixture in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: buttermilk shake for dieters
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend well.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Make favorite bake custard recipe in custard cup.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of Grape-Nuts to each cup.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add about 1/4 cup of the sugar to keep them stiff; set aside.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine the sugar, softened butter, dates and egg; mix well in pan, then cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.
Add the Rice Krispies and nuts (cereal). Form into small balls; roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: spinach, artichoke and mushroom dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Thaw spinach, drain and squeeze out all excess liquid. Dice artichoke hearts into quarters.

Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1/4 C. Parmesan cheese. Transfer to oven safe baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes, remove from oven, add remaining 1/4 C. Parmesan cheese on top and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Heat butter and oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add carrots, celery, onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and green beans; simmer 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and parsley; simmer 10 minutes. Spoon into soup bowls; sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: american moussaka
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, oregano, cinnamon and garlic powder.
Grease baking dish 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch.
Layer half each of the potatoes, beef mixture and cheese in dish; repeat.
Mix sauce mix, milk and water; stir in eggs gradually.
Pour milk-egg mixture over cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise.
Lay cream side up in pan.
Slice bananas in half lengthwise and layer on top of Twinkies.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Put whipped Pet milk over pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: pacos
directions: Soft-fry potatoes; drain.
Cook hamburger and follow directions on taco seasoning package, but lessen water to accommodate juice of tomatoes.
When done, add tomatoes, potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Heat flour tortillas; fill with meat mixture and wrap up.
Can be served with sour cream, guacamole and picante sauce.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter cream cookie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Gently fold in crushed cookies.
Pour batter in pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Wash roast under faucet, dry with paper towels, place on clean paper towels.
Shake garlic salt over roast, both sides, until well covered.
Give both sides several shakes of black pepper, then spray both sides with Pam.
Spray bottom of heavy dutch oven; place roast in dutch oven and put in hot oven, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour in hot water to the side of roast, not over the top of roast, being careful not to let steam burn you.
Place lid on dutch oven and return to oven.
Turn oven temperature down to 175 degrees.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, turning once after first hour.
Cool 10-15 minutes; remove to serving platter and slice.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cube apples and put them in a large pot.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes. Stick fork in apples to check for softness.
Mash apples, add lemon juice and the apple juice.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Heat peanut butter.
Add Tabasco to flavor.
(It's supposed to taste kind of spicy hot.)
Great with Nassi, French fries and chicken.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and allow to cool.
Toss celery, cheese and drained pimento with the cooled macaroni.
Fold in sandwich relish until all ingredients are coated.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine grated cucumber and tomatoes and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and spices in heavy pot.
Add cabbage, onions, tomatoes and cucumber.
Boil 18 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place in "hot" jars and seal.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Combine molasses and water; add alternately with flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan with waxed paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: dream dessert
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple juice in a bowl, then add pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges and bananas.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb-custard pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pastry shell.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs; beat well.
Pour the egg mixture into the pastry shell.
To prevent overbrowning, cover edge with foil. Bake in 375° oven 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until pie is nearly set.
(Pie appears soft in the center, but sets upon cooling.)
Cool.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: foster franks
directions: Prepare grill for cooking.
Cut hot dogs on each end 1/2-inch both ways (like an x on each end).
Put hot dogs on grill and cook.
When they are just about done, put on barbecue sauce, then add salt and pepper.
Cook until done.

title: glazed ham
directions: Bake ham until done.
Mix jam and mustard together; pour over ham; return to oven until coating is brown.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar.
Add shortening well.
Add eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and add bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° until it is done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix water with soup, then cook onion in butter.
Pour all in casserole dish, mix well and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grate pears, onions and peppers.
Add other ingredients; cook until tender.
Place in sterilized jars; seal.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter and mix; press in pan.

title: zucchini apple crisp
directions: Core and peel zucchini.
Remove seeds and slice into apple like pieces, about 8 cups.
Place zucchini and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Add nutmeg, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir until sugar melts.
Remove from heat.

title: peanut chewies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup; bring to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Stir in cereal, coconut and peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool thoroughly.
Do not refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: In a large bowl stir all ingredients together.
Spoon into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with non stick cooking spray. Bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add beef (browned and crumbled), flour, salt, pepper, paprika.
Stir well on medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat.
Serve over rice, Chinese noodles or toast.

title: chocolate and peanut butter pie
directions: Chill mixing bowl and beaters.
Beat cream cheese and peanut butter until smooth.
Add 1 Cup powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat until combined.
In the chilled mixing bowl, beat whipping cream and 2 Tbsp. powdered sugar until soft peaks form.
Gently fold about 1/3 of the whipped cream into the peanut butter mixture.
Fold remaining whipped cream and chocolate chips into peanut butter mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Cover, let chill about 2 hours.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute the onions in butter. Add dill weed, salt, pepper, 1/2 cheese and sour cream. Set aside.
Mix Jiffy mix, egg, milk, corn and green chilies.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer onion mixture and put the other 1/2 of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dixieland salad
directions: Place vegetables in a bowl in layers, sprinkling sugar, salt and pepper on each layer. Cover with the vinegar, using more if necessary. Let stand for about an hour before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in bottom of pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: bubble up pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
In a large bowl, mix biscuits, 1 cup sauce, 2 cups cheese, garlic and toppings.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all in large bowl. Mix with electric mixer until well blended, pour into greased baking dish.

title: sugar plums
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar slowly. Add cream and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in colored sugar and dry jello mix or chocolate bits.
Refrigerate. These freeze well.

title: won tons
directions: Put pork, onions and water chestnuts through food chopper (fine blade) or chop well on a cutting board.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: multi-fruit salad
directions: Combine strawberries and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add Fruit Salad Dressing.
Stir to coat well.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put all the ingredients in blender in order listed; cover and run on high, just until all potatoes go through the blender (do not overblend). Pour into casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a double boiler, or a stainless steel bowl set into a pan of water, put chocolate and butter.
Stir till blended.
Remove from heat, add egg yolks, stir until blended.
Place bowl in refrigerator until mixture is slightly cooler then lukewarm (about length of time to whip egg whites).
Don't over chill.
Beat egg whites till soft peaks, gradually add sugar, beating briskly. Continue beating till egg whites stiff.
Fold whites into chocolate mixture and spoon into individual dishes.
Chill till ready to serve.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. 4 servings.

title: gregs dip
directions: Spread bean dip on tray.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle with green onions, tomatoes, black olives and Cheddar.
Serve on tray with Doritos or chips.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Mix everything in order given.
Toss lightly.
Use 8 or more boneless chicken breasts for 6 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and egg yolks; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Add sour cream and flour to butter-sugar-egg mixture alternately, beating well.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook in greased and floured tube baking pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello and sugar. Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Cover with marshmallows.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Chop onion and brown with ground beef.
Add tomatoes, Rotel, beans and hominy and stir well.
Add taco mix and ranch dressing. Salt to taste.
Cook, over medium heat, for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix with milk and whip with mixer.
Let stand 5 minutes; add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding and stir together.
Start with layer of wafers, then pudding mixture, then bananas.
Repeat with same.
Use egg white topping if desired.

title: easy chicken & dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts and reserve broth.
Cube chicken and mix with onion and celery.
Place in a well greased 9 by 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over this.
Combine flour and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Combine 2 cups of chicken broth and 1 can cream soup.
Pour over flour mixture.
Lightly salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: quick squares(no cooking)
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in double boiler.
After all is melted and mixed, add miniature marshmallows.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: grandmomma whisnant's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into walnut-size balls. Press onto cookie sheet with fork.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut cooked chicken into small pieces.
Spray a 9x13-inch oven-proof dish with cooking spray.
Put chicken pieces in dish. Top with eggs and onions.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine all in 1-quart baking dish.
Bake until hot and bubbly.
Great served with crackers (warm).

title: quick blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine berries, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Stir well and set aside.
Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add milk to make batter. Pour over melted oleo.
Spoon berries over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cran-raspberry frost
directions: Combine raspberries and chilled juices.
Scoop sherbet into punch bowl; add chilled lemon-lime soda.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and put into a deep, heavy pot.
Add onion; cook until transparent but not brown.
Add water and potatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 10 minutes.
Add milk, clams, 1 can clam liquid, salt and pepper. Heat just to boiling.
Season to your taste.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: Combine 1 1/3 cups water and soup base. Bring to boil. Add rice; cover and reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Add mushrooms, carrot, water, parsley, onion and pepper to rice. Stir well. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well; add beaten egg.
Add alternately with the other cup of water and remaining flour. Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Punch down and work a little.
Then take off portion needed; make rolls. Cover remaining dough and place back in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several days.
Bake when doubled in size at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Spread evenly in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dishes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.
Serves 8.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients. Recommend using a Bundt pan.
No frosting needed.
Great with Cool Whip!
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Boil sugar and water to a thin syrup.
Press 12 marshmallows into the syrup, but do not stir.
Beat 1 egg white (thick) and when marshmallows are melted, beat into the egg white.

title: broiled crab nibbles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread on French bread slices. Broil until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: crockpot chicken cacciatore
directions: Add all ingredients to crockpot and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours.
Serve over cooked rice or spaghetti noodles.
If desired, you can add mozzarella cheese on the plate and microwave until the cheese melts.

title: shirley clarke's chocolate walnut raw apple cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients. Add eggs and oil, then mix well.
Add walnuts and apples. Stir together.
Pour in greased and floured sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Icing with custard sauce is optional.

title: mexican egg bake
directions: Combine all of the above in a 9 x 13 pan bake at 350 for 35- 40 minutes.
Serve with Salsa.

title: artichoke dip with bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dice artichoke bottoms. Combine ingredients in bowl, keeping 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese for topping. Place mixture into oven-safe glass dish and top with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and serve on pumpernickel bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until thawed. Add pineapples, oranges, fruit cocktail, pie filling and bananas.
Pour into large bowl. Refrigerate until set.
Add miniature marshmallows.

title: pineapple nut cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: christmas crunch salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large salad bowl.
Set aside.
In small bowl, whisk lemon juice, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper until seasonings are dissolved.
Slowly whisk in vegetable oil. Pour over salad; stir to blend.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: trash
directions: Melt together oleo, chip, peanut butter.
Add crispix and mix while it is hot.
Pour sugar in large brown paper (grocery) bag. Add in mix and shake well until all cereal is coated.
Serve in bowl.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Combine roast, wine, broth and onions.
Microwave 4 minutes on High; then 1/2 hour on Simmer (3 power).
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook 45 minutes on 5 (Medium power).

title: brown rice
directions: Cut potatoes (amount depends on size of pan). Season potatoes with season salt. Add Italian seasoning to taste
and diced onions. Cover pan with tinfoil. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Add cream of mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and tuna fish (optional). Bake until brown.

title: mayo muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: In a saucepan, combine cranberries, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, sprinkle gelatine into orange juice to soften, then add to hot mixture.
Cool; chill until syrupy.
Fold in celery, carrots and apples.
Pour into a 6-cup oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and serve.
(Great with poultry.
With cottage cheese, it is a nutritionally complete lunch.)

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix flour, oregano, eggs, salt, pepper and milk until smooth, then spread in lightly greased pan.
Brown hamburger, sausage and onion; season to taste.
Spread over dough.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Drizzle 1 cup pizza sauce on top of this.
Spread the Monterey Jack cheese on pizza.
Bake for 10 or 15 minutes more.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add berries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and mashed banana.
Mix and allow to congeal in refrigerator.
Spoon Cool Whip over top and serve.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Add sugar, syrup and water in pan.
Stir until dissolved.
Add food coloring; do not stir anymore.
Boil about 15 minutes or until thermometer is 310°.
Test for readiness by dropping a bit in cold water.
Pour in lightly buttered pan.
Let sit until hard and cold.
Break up.
Shake pieces in bag with powdered sugar.

title: loaf bread apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice them thin.
Place in a buttered dish and sprinkle with cinnamon; toss with fork.
Cut each slice of bread into 4 long strips.
Arrange the 16 strips of bread on top of apples.
Combine sugar, egg and margarine.
Mix well and pour over bread and apples.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Delicious!

title: chicken with lemon *(ideal for those on a low cholesterol diet)
directions: Cut chicken into 8 pieces.
Remove skin.
Heat oil and margarine.
Gently fry chicken; turn to brown evenly.
Remove chicken to a plate.
Cut celery and carrots into 1 1/2-inch long, thin matchsticks.
Stir carrots, celery and onion into chicken juices.
Cover.
Simmer.
Cook until just about to brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken; bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat. Simmer 35 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Remove to a serving dish (discard bay leaf).
Heat sauce quickly to thicken. Spoon over chicken and garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with rice and a green salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix all in a large bowl.
Store, covered, in refrigerator. Batter keeps 6 weeks.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Set aside to cool.
Mix dressing according to package directions.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add cooled pasta and toss. Mix in dressing according to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Serves 6.

title: tuna sauce
directions: Place egg in blender and whirl at low speed.
Slowly add tuna, lemon juice and salt.
Blend at high speed.
Remove to serving dish and add parsley and capers.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
Next morning, simmer rhubarb mixture 10 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O.
Pour in jam jars and freeze when cooled.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald one quart of milk in double boiler.
To the hot milk, gradually add the cornmeal.
Cook for 15 minutes; stir constantly. Add molasses, salt, ginger and well beaten eggs.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Put in cold milk just before putting into oven.
Stir only slightly.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake 2 hours in moderate oven.
Stir occasionally.
This pudding should whey and will not do so if baked too fast.
Serve hot or cold or topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: green ricegroves, texas
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add broccoli to rice, pour into a greased 1 qt. casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter and let stand 10 minutes.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Mix well and add apples and pecans.
Stir well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Serves 10.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Cook beef in butter, stirring, until brown and crumbly.
Add onion and celery and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes (break with fork), water, salt, chili and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Add cabbage.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender (about 3 minutes).
Serve in soup plates.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Layer ingredients in baking dish: Doritos, meat, beans, soup (mix tomatoes and green pepper with soup).
Layer all ingredients until gone.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: taco-bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer one hour.

title: lattice-top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions.
Spread mixture into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: In large bowl or blender, beat eggs and cottage cheese until smooth.
Beat in flour and salt.
Drop by tablespoons onto hot griddle sprayed with non-stick coating.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Serve with Mandarin orange slices.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Contains 95 calories per 1/4 cup.
Good with beef, pork and chicken.

title: lancaster county corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, salt, sugar, cornstarch and milk with an electric beater.
Add corn and continue to mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole and top with dots of butter.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes until "set" when you shake casserole and until it is lightly browned on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave popcorn balls
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Cook 6 minutes on High; stir after 2 1/2 minutes. Stir when done and pour mixture over popped corn in large pan; butter bottom of pan for easier removal of corn.
Mix thoroughly and pour all into a clean large brown paper sack.
Fold top down and lay in microwave.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High. Shake sack well and put back for 45 seconds on High. Shake well and pour all into pan.
Quickly form balls. Butter hands well.
Makes 11 to 12 average size popcorn balls.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg and milk together and add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of a funnel; pour in some batter.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into pan filled with 1-inch of hot oil. Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove from pan and drain on a paper towel.

title: dolly parton's banana pudding
directions: Layer sliced bananas and vanilla wafers in large baking pan. Mix together sugar, flour, eggs, butter and salt in heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Add the milk, a little at a time.
Cook slowly until the mixture thickens.
Let it cool for a few minutes, then add the vanilla.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour. Salt to taste.

title: party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, place sherbets.
Pour ginger ale over all.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, onion and celery, whole or cut up.
Simmer 1 hour. Add carrots. Simmer 30 minutes more.
Remove chicken.
Clean and cut up.
Add 2 cups water and bouillon. Return chicken. Add noodles.
Best if served hot on a rainy day.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar
and
oil
and beat thoroughly. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt
and
cinnamon
into first mixture and beat well.
Fold in carrots.
Pour
into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: In bowl, combine well the beef,
2 tablespoons of Parmesan, parsley, bread crumbs, salt and pepper to taste and half the egg, reserving remainder for another use.
Form mixture into marble size balls.
In a large, heavy saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon of oil over moderately high heat and saute the meat balls until just firm to the touch and browned lightly, about 3 minutes.
Transfer with slotted spoon to plate.

title: chocolate cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350 for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue beef on french bread
directions: Boil beef stew meat for 2 hours until tender (very). Cool, then take and shred meat, tearing into small pieces.
Squeeze orange into small bowl.
Set aside.
Dice onion.
Place meat and onion in skillet. Stir on low heat for about 3 to 5 minutes until meat starts to brown. Add remaining ingredients to skillet.
Let simmer about 5 to 7 minutes.
Place beef on bread.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Place cream cheese in a bowl; gradually add all other ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk. Let stand 5 minutes. Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff. Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco. Add egg yolks. Alternate flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Fold in egg whites and coconut. Add pecans. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers. Bake at 350°. When toothpick is inserted and comes out clean, cake is done.

title: chocolate chip sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Stir together flour and baking soda.
in
mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Beat in sour cream alternately with flour mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into well greased and floured 10 inch fluted tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: company rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute onion and green pepper.
Add rice, stirring until rice loses its color.
Do not brown.
Remove from heat and add mushrooms, pimentos, water chestnuts, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir until blended and pour into the bouillon and water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove, cover and bake another 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix everything together and place in casserole dish and let sit overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Before the 25 minutes are up, place on top of casserole 1 cup grated cheese, (optional) 2/3 cup crushed walnuts or cashews or a handful of crushed potato chips.

title: no crust cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add baking powder and sugar gradually.
Continue beating.
Add vanilla, stir in crushed crackers and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and then refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip and fresh or frozen strawberries or chocolate curls.

title: cheese pie
directions: Bake the pie crust first. Put cottage cheese through sieve and add other ingredients. Bake in moderate oven (350°) until firm in center, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy angel biscuits(very good)
directions: Mix Bisquick and cream in mixing bowl until well blended. Knead slightly on a floured board, about 8 turns, by folding over edges to center.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass edge.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven on an ungreased baking sheet for 10 minutes.
Yield: 14 biscuits. Preparation: 15 minutes.
Baking: 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread slices into pieces.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Cook sausage in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Spoon over bread crumbs.
Spread broccoli and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean. Can be assembled the night before.
Cover and refrigerate, then uncover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cape cod scallops
directions: Layer scallops and crackers in greased casserole.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deer steak and gravy
directions: Slice onion and pepper in rings.
Brown onion and pepper lightly in oil.
Remove and drain.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound into trimmed deer steaks.
Brown on both sides.
Drain off oil.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese set out 1/2 hour.
Use mixer to mix cream cheese with soup until well beaten.
Add onion.
Heat until smooth. Spoon in shrimp and mix (use spoon for the shrimp).
Let set for about an hour.

title: berry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add jello. Fold in berries.
Cool until firm in shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Delicious as a strawberry pie.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all in a saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Can be used for flavoring beans or anything you like.
Store in refrigerator.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Whip together slightly the eggs, milk and seasonings.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 8 to 12-cup casserole. (Important: Must rest overnight in the refrigerator.
This causes the souffle to rise.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot glazed pork chops
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except pork chops. Simmer uncovered 10-15 minutes. Fry or bake pork chops. Arrange in baking dish. Cover chops with sauce. Bake until hot in 300° preheated oven about 20 minutes. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended. Drop by spoonfuls onto hot greased frying pan and brown on both sides.
If too thin, add more flour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt and shortening. Mix well and add flour and buttermilk.
Chill.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 5 days.
Roll out, cut and let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 60 biscuits.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix together with mayonnaise and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Mix soup, sauce and milk.
Layer in large baking dish the chips, beef, half the onion and half the cheese.
Pour half soup mixture over all.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: junk cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix 10 minutes (very important). Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes in tube pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in pan; let melt, then combine sugar, milk and flour.
Pour in pan, then add peaches. Bake until golden brown.

title: reddy family sauce
directions: Puree tomato paste and tomatoes in blender.
Add garlic, Italian seasoning and water.
Mix together and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Make meatballs with bread crumbs, egg and ground beef.
Add to sauce 45 minutes before serving.
For less fat, brown meatballs before adding to sauce.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine, and place in glass casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers and stir in margarine. Place on top of mixture and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: burger in cream of mushroom soup
directions: Mix meat, egg, seasoning, bread crumbs, onion and soup.
Make patties and brown in skillet on both sides (Pam or water).
Take patties out of skillet and drain grease.
Add the rest of cream of mushroom soup and mushroom bits and pieces.
Put patties back in skillet; cover and put on low fire for 20 minutes.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute mushrooms until tender.
Remove from pan. Combine flour and pepper.
Coat veal with flour mixture. Brown veal in remaining margarine, a few pieces at a time, until done.
Remove from pan. Add sherry and water to skillet, stirring until liquid is slightly thickened.
Return veal and mushrooms to pan to heat through. Arrange on a serving platter and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: strawberry-peach cobbler
directions: Layer the peaches and strawberries in a shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of the butter.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix Crispix and M&M's.
Break up pretzels and put in jar of peanuts.
Mix around.
Melt all of white chocolate and mix in with the rest of ingredients until coated.
Spread on wax paper until real thin.
Let it set until hard, then break it up.

title: beef kabobs over lemon rice
directions: Combine beef and vegetables in large plastic food bag with zippered closing.
Add dressing and marinate 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Remove beef and vegetables from marinade.
Heat reserved marinade to a boil.
Alternately thread beef and vegetables onto 4 skewers.
Grill or broil kabobs, turning and basting with marinade 5 to 7 minutes or to desired doneness.

title: egg souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: homestyle cannelloni classic
directions: Preheat
oven
to
brown beef and onion together until done.
Pour off fat.
Lay out lasagna noodles individually. Sprinkle each noodle with spinach, Mozzarella, Parmesan, oregano and meat mixture.
Roll noodle entirely up to resemble a
jelly roll.
Place
seam	side
down
in baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce
over
rolled-up lasagna.
Top with remaining 1/2 Mozzarella cheese. Cover with foil; bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, soup, carrots, onion and chicken.
Spread over broccoli. Mix croutons with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and oil with enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Drop strips one at a time into hot chicken broth.
If you don't have a chicken, add a can of cream of chicken soup.

title: herbed-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut thin slice off bottom of each tomato. Scoop out pulp with small spoon; discard pulp. Invert tomatoes onto paper towels to drain. Combine cottage cheese, green onion, chervil, dill and lemon pepper in small bowl. Spoon into tomatoes. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 8 hours. Makes 5 servings. Calories: 27; Carbohydrate: 3 g.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in casserole and top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and cheese crescents
directions: Flatten out each crescent roll. Fill wide end of each triangle with chicken and grated cheese. Roll up each crescent and pinch together. Place in 8-inch greased casserole dish. In a saucepan over medium heat, combine soup, milk and 1 cup grated cheese. Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Pour over crescents and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swedish brown bread
directions: In saucepan, mix water, milk, bacon grease and molasses.
Heat to lukewarm. Sift 4 cups flour, sugar and salt together.
Sprinkle yeast over this.
Add the lukewarm mixture and beat with a mixer until smooth.
Gradually add 5 cups flour or until you have a stiff dough.
Knead until not sticky on floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl in a warm place and let rise until double in bulk. Punch down; knead.
Make into 4 loaves.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Rub top with butter.
Yield: 32 servings.
Carbohydrate 45 g, protein 4.4 g, fat 2 g, calories 215.

title: farm biscuits
directions: Mix all
ingredients into dough.
Roll on flat surface. Cut out and
place
on	bottom	of
Dutch oven. Cover and bake about 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: baked fresh peaches
directions: Mix together honey, lemon juice and water.
Wash peaches. Peel, cut in halves and remove pits.
Arrange peach halves in two-quart casserole dish.
Pour honey mixture over peaches.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake, covered, 1/2 hour or until tender.
Serve warm or cold, with or without light cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kathy's dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 cake pan. Dump pineapple. Add cherry pie filling. Spread dry cake mix over pineapple and pie filling. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over top. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cookie mix, peanut butter packet from
mix and egg whites in a large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle peanuts over the dough.
Press lightly.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool completely in pan or on wire rack.
Combine confectioners sugar, water and vanilla extract in small bowl.
Stir until blended.
Drizzle glaze over top.
Cut into bars.

title: baked stuffed cod
directions: Place cod in casserole dish (square dish).
Brush with mayonnaise to coat thinly.
Mix crumbs with butter and add shrimp. Place crumb mixture over half of the fillets.
Fold fillets over and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until fish flakes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Prepare all ingredients and layer on a large platter in the order listed. Blend chili beans in blender; add more juice if needed. Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix. Layer the next 4 ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips tucked under the edge of the mixture on the plate. To eat, just dip chips and enjoy!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Add bananas and milk; stir in nuts. Bake in a loaf pan at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry-go-round
directions: Heat pineapple juice and water to boiling.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Cool gelatin mixture until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in pie filling, pineapple and marshmallows. Pour into mold and chill until firm.
May garnish with swirl or whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Yields 12 servings.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Use 10-inch tube pan well-greased.

title: dot garrick's fudge filling
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook until it forms soft ball in cup of cool water.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool to lukewarm and beat with mixer about 5 minutes.
Spread on cake, cupcakes, etc.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into ready to fill pie crust.
Makes
2 pies.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Pour over Crispix and fold in carefully.
Lay on open paper bag and allow to dry (approximately 30 minutes).
Break apart while drying. Pour into a paper bag and shake with 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a cast-iron pan, heat 1 teaspoon butter or margarine in oven for 1 minute.
Add batter.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs; mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Combine thoroughly; do not beat.
Grease loaf pan (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool; remove from pan when slightly warm.
Wrap in foil to seal in moisture and freshness.

title: pear butter
directions: Wash pears; remove stems and quarter.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook until tender.
Put pears through food sieve or food processor.
Add sugar to pulp and mix well.
Place in uncovered shallow pan and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally. Pour into jars and seal.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce and garlic juice.
Simmer for about 25 minutes.
Cook a 5 or 6 oz. package of noodles as directed.
Make a white sauce of sour cream,
cream cheese and chopped green onions (can use white onions).
Put layers of noodles, ground beef, and sauce into a casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheddar cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread with bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix top six ingredients in order.
Set aside.
Fry bacon in skillet on top of stove, when bacon is done on both sides, not crispy, but not raw.
Place cornbread mix on top of bacon.
Let stand on stove top long enough for bottom to settle.
Then
place
in oven until top is golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in loaf pans or 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: In a pan, brown hamburger.
Mix together other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix in hamburger.
Bake in a 325° oven until potatoes are done.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover the cucumbers and onions with ice water and salt (use 1/4 cup salt to 1 quart water).
Refrigerate for 48 hours.
Drain and rinse lightly.
Mix the sugar and vinegar; stir well before adding to cucumbers and onions.
Put pickles in freezer containers.
Cover with liquid and freeze.

title: zack's favorite taco salad
directions: Fry hamburg and drain.
After draining hamburg follow directions on taco mix package.
Once taco and hamburg are mixed, place in a large bowl.
Break up taco shells and add to hamburg mixture with the lettuce.
Stir up, then add Catalina dressing and cheese.
Enjoy.
Serve cool.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind all vegetables coarsely.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture and heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Boiling water bath 10 minutes. Makes 8 pints.

title: tim and mary's oriental morral stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry in heated oil the garlic, onion and rest of spices; add meat. Cook 2 minutes. Steam veggies with soy and water. When veggies are between tender and crispy, add meat and onions.

title: blushing rose punch
directions: Combine Hawiian punch, lemon juice and sugar.
Blend well and chill.
To serve, pour over ice ring in punch bowl, add chilled ginger ale, then gently stir in sherbet.
Garnish with fruit. Yields 30 (punch cups).

title: classic potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes; cool.
Peel eggs and chop, then peel potatoes and cube.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper until smooth.
Add celery, onion, eggs and potatoes.
Toss to coat well.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate-banana milkshake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in electric blender.
Process until just smooth, stopping to scrape sides of container.
Stir in drink mix, if desired.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Place cooked broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake until light brown about 20 minutes.

title: arnice gunter's chicken casserole
directions: Line one large or two small casserole dishes with Escort crackers (use 1/2 box to line dish, save other half to use on top of casserole).
Combine chicken, soups, sour cream and water chestnuts; mix well.
Pour over crushed crackers and top with remaining crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 100 very good cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy licking cake
directions: Mix together for 4 minutes and pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch or 2 layer cake pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar, water and cornstarch and cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and cool. Pour mixture over strawberries and chill in refrigerator. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat thoroughly.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and zucchini.
Bake in regular size bread pan for 55 minutes at 325°.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion in juice drained from peas. Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased casserole dish. Cover with 1 (8 ounce) Cheez Whiz.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with ground beef; season with salt and pepper. Place onions over hamburger. Mix the soups together and spread over meat. Place frozen French fries over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage; drain grease.
Break up sausage. In a bowl, mix together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Tear bread into small pieces and add to egg mixture.
Add cheese and sausage.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onion, pepper and stewed tomatoes fine.
Add salsa.
If you like it hot, get La Victoria hot salsa.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Bake in casserole 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: mom's frito pie
directions: Brown meat, 1/2 cup of onion, salt and pepper. When done drain fat. Add tomato sauce and chili powder. Simmer for 15 minutes. Put on tortilla on bottom of round baking dish. Pour some of the meat over the shell. Then sprinkle cheese over the meat. Repeat this method until all is used. I sprinkle cheddar cheese on the last shell. Bake in oven until cheese is melted at 300°.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Cover and chill dough one hour.

title: crab cakes deluxe
directions: Break crabmeat up finely. Toss with next 6 ingredients.
Stir in sauce which is made as follows:
Melt butter. Stir in flour and seasonings. Add milk and stir constantly until mixture forms a ball. Add to crabmeat combination. Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Shape into cakes.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in melted shortening.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 3/4 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal.
Mix and let stand 5 minutes; drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Coconut or raisins may be added.

title: lemon bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the butter, flour and confectioners sugar.
Pat evenly over pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Five minutes before crust is done, mix together the eggs, sugar, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Pour mixture over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes. Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars before completely cool.

title: nut horns
directions: Rub flour and oleo together.
Mix water, egg yolk, sugar and yeast together.
When ready, add to flour and oleo.
Divide into small balls.
Roll out onto floured surface.
Spread with nut filling.
Cut into wedges like a pie.
Roll, starting with wider end.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes if small, at 350° if a big roll. Rub with egg and sugar before baking.

title: green rice
directions: Mix rice, parsley, cheese, onion, green pepper and garlic. Blend rest of ingredients together, then stir into rice mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until like soft custard when inserted with knife blade.
Use 2-quart casserole, sprayed with Pam.

title: mom's poor man's dish
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
In separate pan, brown ground beef and diced onion; drain fat.
Drain liquid from canned goods, then mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese to garnish top.

title: ranch roll-ups
directions: *Do not use Aztec flour tortillas (no good).

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and margarine together for 5 minutes, then add soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Place in shallow pan (well greased) and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice up squash and cook in boiling water for 5 minutes or so. Drain.
Combine soup, onion, carrot and sour cream.
Fold into drained squash, carefully, so as not to break up squash.
Combine melted margarine and stuffing mix.
(Toss together until moist.) Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix into bottom of 8 x 8-inch lightly greased casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over, then top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; cover with cheese slices.
Pour undiluted soup over cheese; top with stuffing (about 1/2-inch thick).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: candied squash
directions: Cook until squash are done and just a lite syrup left in pan.

title: ground beef and sausage dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients; put in slow cooker.
Set cooker on low.
Serve from slow cooker. Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 3 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Put in buttered casserole.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hard luck dinner
directions: Cook chicken gizzards until soft.
Do not drain fluid.
Add elbow
noodles or flat or dumpling noodles and cook.
Add 1 to 2 cans of mushroom soup.
Serves 5 people.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter; add vegetables and saute.
Add flour and cornstarch.
Add stock and milk.
Add soda, cheese and seasonings. Heat thoroughly but do not boil.

title: lace cookies
directions: Place oatmeal in a mixing bowl; melt margarine and pour over oats.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix the dry ingredients with the oats.
Beat egg and add vanilla to egg.
Blend with the oats.
Add pecans.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil and drop cookies by 1/2 teaspoonful.
Bake at 325° for 11 minutes.
Cool before removing from foil.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses come to room temperature.
Mix gradually with dressing mix.
Mixture will be sticky. Shape into ball.
(Since mixture is sticky, I use plastic bags on my hands to roll.) Roll in chopped pecans, if desired. This makes a large ball and I sometimes make two smaller balls.
Place in refrigerator until serving time.
Serve with crackers.

title: french fried almonds
directions: Heat oil in a deep fryer to 360°.
Fry dry blanched almonds in oil until lightly browned, using a deep fryer basket or strainer for easy handling.
Drain almonds on absorbent paper and sprinkle with salt while hot.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and jello together.
Drain peaches.
Add marshmallows.
Chill at least one hour.

title: foods for the gods
directions: Warm in pan the thin cream.
Add beaten yolks and pinch of salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 8 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix only until dissolved.
Add walnuts last.
Grease a cookie sheet well and spread on it (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet).

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bottom only of 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas, milk and vanilla; blend well.
In small bowl, combine flour, nuts, soda and salt; mix well.
Add to banana mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Bring to a boil the meat and above ingredients.
Simmer and stir occasionally; cook for 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Saute onion, mushrooms and celery in dry Vermouth.
Mix Stove Top dressing by package directions.
Add sauteed onions, mushrooms and celery to dressing mix.

title: golden squash cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Onto sheet of wax paper, sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs and sugar until combined.
Add sour cream, orange peel and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in squash and dates.
Spray Bundt pan before adding batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert cake onto wire rack.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
In small mixing bowl, combine confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Add juice. Mix well.
Pour over cooled cake.

title: fruited tea
directions: Put this in gallon jug; mix and finish filling with water.

title: skillet ham, pineapple and peppers
directions: Stir-fry ham in margarine 3 to 5 minutes until lightly browned. Add pineapple and green peppers.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until peppers are crisp-tender.
Mix all other ingredients.
Stir into skillet and heat, stirring until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Make tray up of raw vegetables.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until the yolks are hard (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain and cool in cold water.
Peel eggs.
Cut eggs in half.
Remove the yolks.
Sift the yolks.

title: jennifer's favorite fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and box of jello until well blended.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Best if made ahead of time and allowed to chill for several hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake with frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° until done.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms, vinegar, oil, onion, seasonings and sugar in large pot.
Boil for 3 minutes; drain in colander.
Combine red wine, vinegar, salad oil, onions, salt, parsley, mustard and brown sugar and pour over mushrooms in a large bowl.
Marinate at room temperature until cool.
Place, covered, in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Will keep as long as mushrooms last.

title: german christmas cookies
directions: Soak ammonia in milk 24 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut with Christmas cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° to 350° until light brown on bottom and white on top.
Frost and decorate.
Never a failure.
They mellow after frosted and stored in an airtight container.

title: old maid clara's cake
directions: Could add a little almond and/or vanilla extract, if desired.

title: green rice
directions: Saute chopped onion and minced garlic in olive oil or butter. Measure cooked rice and ground parsley into a mixing bowl, then add milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce, Cheddar cheese and slightly beaten eggs.
Add sauteed onion and garlic; mix thoroughly and pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Roll out each biscuit, then put 2 to 3 tablespoons of apple filling in biscuit and fold biscuit over, pressing edges down with fork.
Place in greased baking dish.
Then mix and pour the sugar, cinnamon, margarine and 7-Up over the top of apple biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Cream butter in large bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating at high speed until light and fluffy. By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving, because the cake has a soft fudge interior.
Test for doneness after an hour by observing dry, shiny brownie-type crust.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Cut grapefruit in half crosswise. Scoop out meat and membrane.
Pile chicken mixture into grapefruit halves. Top with cheese and crushed potato chips. Place on a baking sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with rolls.

title: quick zucchini bread
directions: Mix all wet ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Mix together well and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine persimmon pulp, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder; add to persimmon mixture alternately with a combination of the cream, buttermilk and soda.
Coat baking pan well with melted butter; stir remaining butter into persimmon mixture.
Stir in cinnamon.
Stir well and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beefy quiche
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together until browned.
Add garlic, drain any oil.
Sprinkle pie shell with mixture.
Beat eggs and soup together until blended.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add fruit and nuts. Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream to serve.

title: prune cake
directions: Stew prunes in water, enough to cover over 2-inches. Cool and pour 1 cup of the liquid and reserve.
Blend dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.

Add cooled prunes and mix well. Rotate dry ingredients with the cup of prune juice. Pour into angel food pan that has been coated with nonstick spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna strips according to package directions.
Drain. Pour half of spaghetti sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese with eggs, parsley and salt.
Spread cheese mixture on individual lasagna strips.
Roll strips up and arrange, seamside down, in pan on top of sauce.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes before serving.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Mix apples with sugar, butter or margarine and apple spice or vanilla.
Roll out biscuits on sifted flour.
Then add cooked apples, fold and seal edges.
Fry in a skillet until brown on both sides.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Arrange rhubarb in pie shell; sprinkle with jello.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of pie. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: grandma anderson's cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Squeeze through cookie press. Bake at 350° until done.

title: quick caramel icing(heritage recipe)
directions: Bring to a good boil.
Remove from fire; add 1/2 tsp. baking powder and beat until hard enough to put on cake.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Cook ground beef with onion in a large skillet, stirring continually, until the ground beef is browned and crumbly.
Drain in a colander.
Return the ground beef mixture to the skillet. Stir in ketchup, sour cream, salt and garlic powder.

title: quick chicken gravy
directions: Blend flour and milk; add to chicken soup.
Heat slowly to boiling and cook until thickened.
Strain and serve.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: tuna melt deluxe
directions: Prepare tuna as desired.
Butter one side of each slice of bread.
Add tuna, bacon and cheese.
Grill both sides.

title: thrifty coconut cream pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, salt, flour and 1/2 of the milk together in a saucepan.
Stir into rest of milk and cook slowly (5 minutes).
Add mixture to egg yolk and cook for 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and add coconut and pour into pie shell. Top with Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: hummingbird cake 'n' frosting
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat, or cake
will be tough. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Put batter in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes if in a 9 x 13-inch pan or from 30 to 35 minutes if in the 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Remove from oven when done and cool at least 15 minutes before using this special cream cheese icing.

title: impossible cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease a pie plate.
Place all ingredients in a blender or large bowl on high speed for 2 minutes. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until puffed and center is dry, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Stir soup, water and gelatin together and let stand for 10 minutes.
Heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool.
Beat in mayonnaise and cottage cheese with rotary beater.
Fold in shrimp, eggs and onion.
Pour into 6-cup mold or individual salad molds sprayed lightly with Pam.
Chill until firm.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and remove core.
Slice quarters thinly; set aside.
Cut sausage lengthwise in half, then into 1/2-inch chunks.
Set aside.
Fry onion in oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter for 5 minutes.
Add sausage chunks; cook 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and cover pan.
Cook 5 minutes; stir and cover.
Cook 3 minutes; stir again.
Cover; let cool for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, carrot and caraway seed; simmer for 20 minutes.
Thicken with remaining 2 tablespoons butter mixed with the 2 tablespoons of flour.
Serve with horseradish.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Marinate in marinade, which has been boiled.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons water and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill four hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and finely chop 1 cup; reserve.
Combine bacon and onion in a medium glass bowl.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp; stir once.
Drain.
Stir in reserved mushroom stems, bread crumbs, cheese and pepper.
Stuff mushroom caps with bread crumb mixture.
On a glass platter arrange 12 in circular pattern.
Cook covered at High 6 to 7 minutes.
Let stand uncovered 2 minutes.
Serve.
Repeat for remaining mushrooms.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: joaney's whole wheat banana muffins
directions: Combine mashed bananas, brown sugar, oil and eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to banana mixture, mixing to combine.
Bake in muffin pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: creamy ham and eggs
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in mustard and pepper.
Add ham and eggs.
Stir gently.
Place toast on individual serving plates. Spoon ham mixture over toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake according to box directions and pour on top of coconut and pecan mixture.
In saucepan, heat margarine and cream cheese until mixture is warm enough to stir in confectioners sugar. Spoon on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 3/4 hour.

title: mints
directions: Melt butter and mix to the other ingredients, except the flavoring.
Mix this very well and then add peppermint flavoring to taste. Press mixture into mint molds or roll.
Cut into cubes. Add any color of food coloring for any birthday parties, Christmas, Valentine, etc.

title: pot pie
directions: Rinse frozen peas and corn under running water to separate; drain.
Heat butter in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in turkey and vegetables.

title: lime-cream cheese jello
directions: Wipe Jell-O mold down with oil.
Make Jell-O and refrigerate until hard.
Soften cream cheese, then beat.
Add Jell-O gradually.
Add Cool Whip and drained fruit.
Put in Jell-O mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, add onions, pepper, garlic salt, green peppers, celery and salt.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Add liquids and simmer about 2 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
