directions: Cook beef and drain grease. Add onions and shrimp if desired. Cook until meat is done. Add cooked rice and tomato sauce. Cut peppers in half and clean out seeds. Fill peppers with meat mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 350° until peppers are soft. May sprinkle tops of peppers with Tex Joy steak seasoning, if desired.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass casserole with a nonfattening cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: indiana salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and water.
Let set until thick, add drained pineapple.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until they crumble.
Butter 9 x 9-inch pan and put in 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Top with Bisquick mixture and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and serve with vanilla ice cream on top of it.

title: fresh fish in foil
directions: You will need 2
pieces
(18 x 18-inch each) heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: m. e.'s famous pancakes
directions: Add if you wish: strawberries, raspberries, chocolate, bananas, blueberries, shredded coconut, or any to your taste.

title: easy cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Sift flour and soda and add to mixture.
Place small bits of dough rolled in tiny balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Dip small glass in flour and lightly flatten.
Bake 4 minutes or until cookie is brown around edge. Bake at 400°. Cool 1 minute and take up.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil the first four ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla to the chocolate mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Then drop by spoonful on a cookie sheet and cool. Yield:
About 2 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain and put all in crock-pot or in large kettle.
Simmer all day.
Scoop into bowls and top with Cheddar cheese and crushed taco chips.
Optional:
Spoon sour cream and salsa on top.
Great for cold days.
Double if needed.
Makes approximately 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in buttered casserole dish.
Combine milk, eggs, vanilla, sugar and nutmeg.
Pour over bread and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer and pour regular milk to fill line.
Freeze.

title: mary ann's turnips
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, fry bacon for 2 minutes. Stir in turnips, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Reduce heat and cook for 45 minutes, covered.
Add potato and cook for 20 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: migas
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Allow to cool slightly. Stir Tabasco into eggs and pour into skillet. Return to heat. When eggs are almost cooked, add cheese and turn heat to lowest setting. Stir in crumbled tostados. Serve hot with salsa. Serves 2.

title: turtle sundae dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Set aside half of the batter; pour remaining batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan over low heat, melt the caramels, milk and butter.
Remove from the heat and add nuts.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour reserved batter over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool.
Cut into squares.
If desired, top each with a scoop of ice cream and a pecan half.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and light. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk, salt, vanilla and milk. In a small bowl, beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gently fold into milk mixture.
If desired, stir in bourbon or brandy. Chill.
Pour into chilled punch bowl or serving cups. Garnish with nutmeg. Chill any leftovers.

title: garden style spiral (colored) macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over macaroni.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and place into large Tupperware bowl that has a cover.
Stir in small onion, bell pepper, pimentos and black olives.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight or 24 hours, if possible.

title: morning glory french toast(heart healthy)
directions: Heat oven to 500°. Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a small bowl with fork. Dip bread into egg mixture and place on a plate. Lightly grease cookie sheet and heat sheet in oven 1 minute. Remove from oven. Place dipped bread on hot cookie sheet. Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown. Turn bread over; bake 2 to 4 minutes longer or until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Tear into small pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Cook cranberries in all but 1/4 cup water until very soft; rub through fine sieve.
Soften gelatin in remaining water.
Heat sugar and corn syrup to boiling; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Combine all ingredients and beat well for a few minutes to cool and slightly thicken.
Pour into automatic refrigerator tray and freeze quickly, stirring several times during freezing.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan or skillet and bake at 425° until done.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: In double boiler or in microwave, melt cheese.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
If desired, add sausage (hot), which has been browned, crumbled and drained.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amish pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet over high heat, then sear meat on all sides.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine and bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours.
Pull meat apart with fork.
Add catsup and cook 1 more hour.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat flour mixture into butter mixture with mixer or spoon; blend until smooth.
Chill 1 hour or until firm.
Roll small amount of dough at a time, 1/8 inch thick.
Keep remaining dough in refrigerator. Cut with cutters.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked french toast
directions: Cook sugar, butter and syrup until bubbly.

Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place bread slices on syrup mixture (2 layers of bread). Mix milk, eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and salt in blender. Pour egg mixture over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve warm or syrup hardens. Can be reheated.

title: smoked fish
directions: Soak fish in cold brine 12 to 18 hours.
Rinse fish; pat dry. Smoke fish 8 to 12 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and tear spinach.
Place in bowl.
Mix balance of ingredients and toss into spinach.
Serve chilled.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a bowl combine dry cake mix, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
In an 8-inch glass baking dish, spoon cherry pie filling into bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix mixture evenly over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes or until topping is no longer doughy.
Rotate dish during cooking if cake does not appear to be rising evenly.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream on top.
Great quick, easy dessert for that last minute.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add broccoli to this mixture, and mix well again. Pour mixture into casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cold green salad soup
directions: Place thawed peas in large heatproof bowl.
Add snow peas and set aside.
In saucepan, over moderate heat, bring chicken stock to a boil and pour over peas and snow peas.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Toss together macaroni, celery and onion. Mix balance of ingredients to make dressing. Add about 1/2 dressing to salad and continue adding until you have right consistency. Stir in tuna.

title: vinegar provencale
directions: Try as a flavorful pick me up for vegetables (add about a tablespoon to cooking water or sprinkle on after cooking), seafood as a marinade or sprinkled after cooking, or salads.

title: "lite" chili
directions: In crock-pot, layer in pot in order given in recipe.
Cook 2 hours on high.
Stir.
Cook 6 more hours on low heat.
On range/stove top, simmer all for 3 to 5 hours.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pat half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crock pot enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion, pour off grease. Put all ingredients in crock pot except Dorito chips. Mix and cook low 4 to 6 hours. Last 15 minutes before you are ready to eat, add Dorito chips and stir.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle pretzels
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels in water.
Dip half of each pretzel into the hot caramel.
Place on a greased sheet of foil to cool.

title: okra soup(use big soup pot)
directions: Cover beef with 3 inches water, bay leaves and pepper. Rolling boil 1 hour.
Add okra, onions, tomatoes and paste; bring to rolling boil.
In 30 minutes add butter beans and corn.
Cook 30 minutes and add salt and black pepper to taste.
Can thin down. Also good to can.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Good to dip hamburgers, hot dogs, steak or chicken before barbecuing.
Also good to use as chip dip.

title: cheese beef logs
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and horseradish. Stir in olives.
On wax paper, shape into two 6 x 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll each "log" in snipped dried beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 6 wedges.
Cook in salted water until tender (do not overcook).

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit.
Save juice from peaches, pineapple and apple rings to make 2 cups.
Add cornstarch, sugar and butter to juice and cook until thickened.
Arrange fruit attractively in long casserole dish.
Pour thickened sauce over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with any beef or chicken main dish.
Serves 6 to 8.
Very colorful and pretty to serve.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix cinnamon, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour. Peel and thinly slice apples.
Place in bowl with sugar mixture. Chop apricots and toss with apples and sugar mixture.
Set aside.

title: thin spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Pour sauce over cooked spaghetti and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ann ramey's speedy batter rolls
directions: Pour lukewarm water into a slightly warm mixing bowl. Dissolve yeast.
Stir well.
Add milk, shortening, egg and dry ingredients.
Mix on low speed until all ingredients are blended. Beat 2 minutes at moderate speed.
Cover with waxed paper.
Set in a warm place and let it rise until double in bulk.
Beat 20 or 30 strokes by hand and drop by spoonfuls into muffin pans.
Cover again and let rise until batter reaches top of pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Scoop out potato from the skin and beat with butter until creamy.
Add cocoa and sugar gradually, then add the nuts.
Knead until it can be molded.
Pack into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: quick and easy pineapple frosting
directions: Mix and cook until thickened, which takes about 5 minutes. Spread on any yellow layer cake.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine catsup, vinegar, fat or salad oil, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Bring to boiling point, stirring occasionally. Cook 3 minutes.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain peaches, pears and pineapple, reserving juice.
Pour juice into a medium saucepan.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and curry powder; stir into fruit juice.
Cook juice over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir all fruit into hot mixture.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot. Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: transparent apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and beat until dissolved.
Add one well beaten egg and vanilla.
Fill pie crust with apple slices. Pour mixture over apples and unbaked crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugarless pumpkin-oatmeal bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine pumpkin, sugars, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Mix flour, soda, spices and oats.
Stir into pumpkin mixture with water, raisins and nuts.
Put in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: russian tea cakes or mexican wedding balls
directions: Mix butter, vanilla and sugar thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill dough; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet (cookies do not spread).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set but not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sticky pecan ring
directions: Combine 1st four ingredients in saucepan.
Melt margarine and ingredients over low heat, stirring occasionally, until fully melted.
Spoon 1/4 of this mixture into lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Separate biscuits and arrange in pan.
Stand each on edge and slightly touch together.
Sprinkle cinnamon lightly between each biscuit, then spoon remaining mixture over and between the biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan, then put on serving plate.

title: filled rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes. Stir in scalded milk, oil and rest of the sugar.
Let it cool a bit, then add the beaten eggs.
Add the yeast in the warmed water, then flour, little by little.
Knead the dough until it is soft.
Set this aside in the bowl with a towel over it.
Let it rise.
Roll out the dough and fill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain well spinach.
Add water chestnuts, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Then add mayo to make the thinness desired.
Make 24 hours in advance.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients listed.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Serve with hot rolls and salad.

title: zero cholesterol carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, powder, salt and ginger. Drain pineapple well; reserve juice.
In medium bowl, whisk drained pineapple, brown sugar, egg substitute, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Stir pineapple mixture, carrot, zucchini and raisins into flour mixture until flour is moistened.

title: mama's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, salts and bay leaf until chicken is tender. Strain broth and add soup.
Remove skin and debone chicken.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of potatoes and half of onion rings in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half of flour, salt and pepper. Dot with butter.
Add remaining potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with the rest of the flour, salt and pepper and then dot with margarine.
Pour milk over the dish.
Bake, uncovered, in the oven 1 hour at 400°.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between crackers.
Melt almond bark in microwave for 3 minutes, stir in chocolate chips and melt 1 minute more.
Stir.
Dip crackers in chocolate with tongs, and place on wax paper.
Yummy.

title: thick crust pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Then mix all the ingredients together.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Put dough in lightly oiled bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Add all ingredients to melted butter, beginning with sugar. Mix well. Pour into a deep dish pie crust. Bake at 425 degrees for 5 minutes. Then lower oven to 350 degrees and cook for 35 minutes or until done.

title: kaye's corn
directions: Mix all and heat in microwave.

title: chop suey
directions: Chop meat into bite size pieces and cook in small amount of oil for about 20 minutes.
Chop celery into small chunks and cook in fry pan about 15 minutes.
Chop onions and cook about 20 minutes.
Combine all above and stir in molasses.
Cook about 20 minutes then add bean sprouts and toss with soy sauce.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: cinnamon ice cream
directions: Combine milk, 1 cup sugar, cream, cinnamon and salt in heavy saucepan. Bring almost to a simmer over medium-high heat. Whisk egg yolks and 1/4 cup sugar in large bowl. Gradually whisk in hot mixture; return to saucepan and stir constantly over low heat until custard thickens, about 4 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl. Set in another large bowl of ice water. Cool 30 minutes, stirring often. Cover and chill overnight.
Strain custard and process in ice cream maker.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, white sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix the chocolate chips to mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until good and brown.

title: fandango
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano.
Saute a bit longer.
Spoon into a 2-quart flat casserole.
Stir in spinach, soup, sour cream, rice, salt and pepper.
Lay cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 generously.

title: "no guilt" carrot and applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and spices.
Set aside. In medium bowl, combine applesauce, eggs and egg substitute.
Mix well.
Mix with flour mixture.
Stir in carrots.
Pour batter into a 9-inch tube pan greased with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack.

title: potato cheese casserole(microwave)
directions: In bowl, mix soup, cheese, milk, pepper and garlic.
In 2-quart casserole dish, arrange half the potatoes, 1/2 the onions and 1/2 of the soup.
Repeat layers.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 25 minutes.
Rotate dish 3 times during cooking.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini with peanuts
directions: Steam
or
microwave
the zucchini until tender.
Drain and cut
into pieces.
Set aside, but keep warm.
Heat peanut oil
in a skillet and add half of the apricots (drained), the avocado pieces,
1	tablespoon
lemon
juice, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook
or 4 minutes or until well heated.
Mix with the hot zucchini.

title: flowerpot surprise
directions: You will need an 8 to 10-inch in height flowerpot and plastic or silk flowers.

title: lola cummins braley's blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and berries.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg, sifted together.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° until center springs back on touch.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stuffing mix.
Mix margarine with stuffing mix.
Line bottom of pan with stuffing mix.
Pour other ingredients over stuffing.
Put 1/4 package of corn bread stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Mix coconut, milk, powdered sugar, margarine and sliced or broken almond pieces in a bowl.
Use your hands or spoon to mix up ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Chill small rolled up balls for 3 hours or overnight.
Melt semi-sweet chips in a double boiler.
If chocolate chips become to thick add cap full of oil to chocolate.
Stir.
Insert toothpick in top of candy mixture and dip in chocolate.
Tap candy against spoon to get excess off of candy then place on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in the margarine with a pastry blender or fork until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture for the topping.
Stir the baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon into remaining mixture.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the cream cheese and the margarine until smooth.
Add the chicken and remaining ingredients and stir.

title: new orleans jambalaya
directions: Put rice in heated oil in heavy saucepan; stir until lightly brown.
Add minced ingredients and saute for a few minutes.
Add boiling water, oyster juice, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly. Add oysters, stir once and reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice hard-boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks to a mixing bowl and crumble with a fork.
Stir in enough mayonnaise and mustard to wet yolks.
Add a dash of pepper and the onion powder.
Mix until combined.
Spoon into egg centers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover to refrigerate until serving time.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cut peeled peaches into small chunks.
Put into medium mixing bowl.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Stir.
Let stand about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
You should have 1 cup of syrup; if not, add orange juice to make 1 cup.
Put in medium saucepan.
Add cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and extract.
Cool.
Pour over peaches and stir.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Prepare other ingredients and mix well with pasta, dressing and Salad Supreme.
Refrigerate overnight and set at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: penuche
directions: Cook milk, sugars, corn syrup and salt until softball stage or 236 degrees. Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool to lukewarm and add vanilla. Beat and add nuts.

title: lima dill salad
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions, then drain beans and chill thoroughly.
Mix cooled lima beans with celery, green onions and parsley.
Blend mayonnaise, vinegar, dill seed, salt and pepper.
Pour mayonnaise mix over lima bean mix and toss to coat beans.
Refrigerate.
Serve on salad plate lined with lettuce.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Sprinkle onion and mushroom soups over all.
Seal securely with foil.
Bake at 275 degrees for 4 hours.
Makes its own gravy.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Stir as it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 5 more minutes without stirring. Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Put into shallow pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Remove and cool. Break apart and store in a tightly covered container.

title: huge scary spiders
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly grease baking sheet. In a saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat. Let cool. In a small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, beat margarine on low speed until smooth and add sugar and beat until creamy. Stir in egg, vanilla and chocolate. Add flour mixture. Mix well until a stiff dough forms.

title: caramel crunch
directions: Melt caramels plus 1/2 stick butter and milk in top of double boiler.
Pour over crushed cornflakes and chopped pecans.
Mix together and press into medium size baking dish.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.
Frost when cool.
Double recipe to make 2 sheet cakes.

title: microwave potato supreme
directions: Slice potatoes and onion and lay in microwavable casserole dish.
Place pats of butter over potatoes and sprinkle Season-All over the potatoes.
Cook in microwave at Full power for 10 minutes.
Check for tenderness.
Cover with cheese and cook 2 more minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips, crackers or Melba rounds as dippers.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Mix rest.
Line baking dish with corn chips.
Now layer the meat, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix ammonia, Dawn and alcohol together and pour into gallon container and finish filling with water.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, pie spice, salt and baking soda. Mix together oil, pumpkin and walnuts.
Blend flour and oil mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cover with foil for last 30 minutes.

title: guess again cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten by pressing with bottom of drinking glass, greased and dipped in sugar.
(Grease and sugar glass as needed.) Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 10 to 11 minutes.
Remove to racks to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until a little rubbed between your fingers no longer feels grainy.* Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet, covered with foil. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 35 cookies.

title: healthy macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on box; set aside.
Saute onion, peppers and garlic in a deep frypan.
Add ground turkey and brown thoroughly.
Drain off any fat and add tomato sauce and spices. Return to heat for 5 minutes and mix well.
In a casserole dish (greased) combine macaroni and turkey tomato sauce with 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: grinath chocolate cookies
directions: Bake same as Lemon Cookies except use no lemon flavoring and add cocoa, vanilla and only 2 1/2 cups flour.
Cream butter and sugar, adding eggs (one at a time).
Add flavoring.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into thick roll and slice or roll flat.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.Mix butter, sugar, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: tremendous crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat and discard the fat. Combine all the ingredients in crock-pot, stirring well. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
In large mixing bowl, mix butter, both sugars and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put rice in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Chop onion.
Mix all soups together with water. Pour over rice and hamburger meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Melt grated cheese on top last few minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: a short cake(for strawberries or other fruit)
directions: Add beaten eggs to the cold water.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; slowly add to the egg mixture, then add melted butter.
Best made in a flan pan, but an 8-inch round cake pan will do.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens (about 12 minutes).
Add about 1 1/3 cups coconut and 1 cup chopped nuts to mixture.
Beat until frosting is cool and thick. Excellent!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Beat all ingredients 30 seconds with spoon.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 5 minutes. Loosen sides of loaf from pan with knife.
Remove from pan.

title: breakfast cinnamon rolls
directions: Use enough butter to grease a large loaf pan.
Mix remaining butter, brown sugar, pudding mix and cinnamon.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Lay still frozen rolls in rows over mixture.
Cover with a clean dish cloth and put in a cold oven.
Close door.

title: heavenly torte
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using half of required ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and milk, adding milk gradually.
When smooth, add pudding and continue beating until it begins to thicken.
Spread on top of the cooled cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over top of pudding mixture. Spread whipped topping over all.
Top with nuts.
Cover and chill 24 to 48 hours.
Serves 15; freezes beautifully.
Other half of cake mix can be used for cupcakes or to make another torte.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, eggs and water. Add chips; mix. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done.

title: hot cheesy biscuits
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt, baking powder and pepper.
Add cheese and the buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy, then crumble.
Break off tops of broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix together broccoli, cauliflower and bacon.
Then mix together Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar and pour over vegetables; mix well.
Refrigerate after preparing.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Pour over corn immediately.
Form into balls or break into crunch.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, add cream of tartar and beat until they stand in peaks.
Add sugar slowly, then flour which has been sifted several times.
Bake in ungreased pan in 300° oven for 50 minutes.
Do not open oven door for first 20 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot and cook until tender.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 24 biscuits.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Pour 1 Tbsp. oil in pan and cook puree over high flame, stirring.
Add broth, salt (if needed).
Heat 1/2 inch oil and fry tortillas until they begin to stiffen.
Add pinch of oregano to broth 5 minutes before serving.
Add avocado, cheese, and tortillas to serving bowls.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth and creamy. Extra pepper sauce may be added to taste. Serve with corn chips or as an added sauce for Mexican dishes.

title: roast chicken with walnut sauce(to serve 4)
directions: Pat the chicken dry inside and out with paper towels.
Then truss it securely with white kitchen cord.
Mix the melted butter and vegetable oil together and with a pastry brush, coat the chicken thoroughly.

title: joneserella fudge
directions: Mix and cook milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla and let boil for 35 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until the mixture is firm.
Pour into greased pan.
Let cool for 1 hour, then cut and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk, sausage and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, mix 1 can of cream of mushroom soup with a small amount of milk.
Drain 1 can mushrooms.
Pour over rest.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Can use ham instead of sausage.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender (drain).
Add salt margarine and egg. Mix well then add cheese, milk, crackers and pimentos.
Put in bowl, sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and put in oven on about 425° until top gets brown.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat liquids to 120°.
Add to dry mixture.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2) pans, greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place 45 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 package dried beef.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball and cool.
Roll in second package of chopped beef.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: In large bowl, combine corn meal, flour, egg, corn, garlic salt, green onions and buttermilk; stir thoroughly with spoon. Heat fat or oil to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into fat and fry until golden brown on both sides. Serves 15 to 20.

title: chicken pie
directions: Divide pastry in half.
Line a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan with 1 part pastry.
Melt oleo; add flour and seasonings.
Let bubble.
Add liquid and cook slowly until thickened.
Add chicken.
Pour into pan.
Top with pastry.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: barbara's sweet pickles
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: "milk and egg free" macaroni or potato dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in pan.
Add Coffee Rich and water; stir until thick.
Add vinegar and mix well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat milk and eggs with fork.
Add vanilla and sugar; blend with fork.
Break bread into mixture.
Put cut apple slices on top and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Dab with butter on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Put one vanilla wafer in each.
Combine rest of ingredients except pie filling; mix well. Spoon mixture into tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Remove from pan.
Top with a spoonful of cherry pie filling on each.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Spread pecans on cookie sheet.
Drizzle with melted butter and a little salt. Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Stir. Bake 5 minutes more.
When cool, put in deep bowl.

title: date pinwheel cookies(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Mix all but the dates, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water. Divide and chill.
Cook 1 pound dates with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water until boiling.
Set aside until cool.
Roll out dough as for jelly rolls.
Spread date mixture on the dough and roll up. Chill overnight, then slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar.
Crumble wafers.
Add wafers, coconut and nuts.
Grease a large pan and bake at 275° for about 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and shortening.
Stir in buttermilk and bananas.
Stir together and add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts.
Let set 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 (more or less) minutes in a 9 x 3 x 5-inch pan.

title: hamburger summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into a roll 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil, shiny side in.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.
Next day poke holes in the bottom of the foil with a toothpick.
Pour 1/2 inch of water in the bottom of a roaster pan.
Place about 3 lids (jar) in the bottom of this pan. Put the meat on the lids with the side with the holes on the bottom.
Bake for 90 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with half of shredded beef.
Use remaining half to cover Cheese Ball.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut candy, dates and nuts into small pieces.
Leave cut up overnight in pan.
Sift 2 cups flour over mixture.
Cream butter and sugar with eggs.
Add soda, remaining flour and buttermilk to butter and sugar mixture.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well and bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
While hot, mix 2 cups brown sugar with 1 cup frozen or fresh orange juice and pour over cake.

title: fresh apple cakes
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs, flour and flavoring.
Add apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and put batter in.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: chili sauce for enchiladas
directions: Fry onion and garlic in fat.
Add salt, oregano and chili pulp; add enough water to make a thin gravy.
Boil for 20 minutes. If a milder sauce is desired, add a beaten egg just before removing from heat, or use more flour and less chili powder.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries, orange, apple and nuts.
Add sugar and let stand about 30 minutes.
Fix jello.
Let set until cool.
Mix together and put in mold.
Don't freeze.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie ii
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of Jell-O (3 tablespoons).
Cool.
Add 2 to 3 cups fresh strawberries.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: dumplings for soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour and mix until smooth over low heat.
Add 1 cup boiling water all at once and stir constantly until dough leaves sides of pan; cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well in between.
Add salt.
Drop into boiling water (form dumpling with a teaspoon).
Cook 3 to 5 minutes and place in soup dish or make them ahead of time and heat them in the soup.

title: cutout cookies
directions: With electirc mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugars. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon juice.

title: frozen congealed salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into square container or mold.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in a large pot and strain.
Cut cheese into cubes.

title: simmering kitchen spices(potpourri)
directions: Mix together.
Place a tablespoon of mixture in a small amount of water and simmer on the stove or place on the back of a lighted wood stove.

title: luscious chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, two at a time.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in syrup.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and frost.

title: no bake stuffed peppers
directions: Cook ground meat and chopped onion together in a small amount of oil.
Drain excess moisture and fat off.
Add water, barbecue sauce and Minute rice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese and fill peppers.
Place in skillet with a little water and heat.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Add rice; smooth over pan evenly. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice.
Place pieces of chicken over rice and soup mix.
Salt and pepper slightly.
Pour water over all ingredients.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Heat and mix the chili and cream cheese.
Stir in veggies and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown beef in fat.
When meat is almost done, add onion, green pepper and celery.
Brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour or all day.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Serve with a sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: the au lait
directions: Heat skim milk in mug or 2 cup glass heatproof container for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Place tea bag in and let steep for 4 minutes. Remove tea bag and add extract and if sweetness is desired, Equal.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Place hamburger, pizza sauce, garlic powder, seasoning, salt, pepper and onions in baking dish.
Spread on top of meat mixture, sour cream, then Mozzarella cheese; last crescent rolls.
Bake until rolls are done at 350°.

title: bacon and chicken livers
directions: Cut bacon strips in halves.
Cut chicken livers into about 1-inch pieces.
Wrap one bacon strip around each piece of chicken liver.
Secure each with a wooden toothpick.
Place all in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Broil for about 5 to 10 minutes; turn each over and broil for about 5 to 10 minutes on the other side.
Serve hot.

title: cornish hens and wild rice supreme
directions: After thawing hens, remove giblets.
Rinse and pat dry.
Brush inside and out with melted butter.
Remove seasoning package from rice.
Rub 1 teaspoon seasoning mix per hen inside and out.
Place hen breast-side up, in shallow roasting pan.
Pour chicken broth and 1/2 cup of water in pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and add green onion, mushroom and rice package.
Saute, stirring frequently; slowly add 1 1/4 cups water, rest of seasoning from package, wine and bay leaves.
Bring to boil.
Pour rice mixture into roasting pan (make sure no rice is resting on hens) and brush hen with remaining butter.
Cover loosely with foil.
Reduce over temperature to 350° and bake for an additional 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: cottage cheese salmon salad
directions: In
top
half of double boiler, soak half the gelatin in milk for 2 minutes until softened.
Place over hot water.
Heat until gelatin dissolves.
Combine with cottage cheese, dill and onion. Pour into lightly oiled 1 quart salad mold or loaf pan, place
in freezer
to
chill
minutes until firm.
Combine salmon,
sour cream, celery and lemon juice.
In top of double boiler, dissolve
remaining gelatin.
Add to salmon mix.
Pour over cottage cheese mixture.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours until completely firm.

title: heavenly heart chocolate cake
directions: In small bowl, stir cocoa into water until smooth; set aside. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until fluffy; beat in eggs and cocoa mixture.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add alternately with sour milk to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: In a 12-inch skillet or 4-quart Dutch oven, brown sausage over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving drippings in pan; set sausage aside.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in reserved drippings; remove chicken, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in pan.
Add onion, red or green pepper and garlic to pan; cook until onion is tender.
Stir in uncooked rice, bouillon granules, spices and water; bring to boiling.
Add sausage and carrots.
Arrange chicken on top.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat and saute onions until clear and tender.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs for topping and line dish with remaining crumbs.
Add onions and soup in alternate layers.
Cover the top with beaten eggs and pour mix over the top.
Sprinkle grated cheese and reserved cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: fabulous chocolate fudge
directions: Chop or shave the Hershey bars.
In a large mixing bowl, place the chocolates, marshmallows and vanilla.
Set aside.
Cook the margarine, sugar and Milnot.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over the chocolate mixture and stir until all is melted.
Keep stirring until it starts to thicken and then pour into a buttered cake pan.

title: carrots with orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Place carrots in a 2 qt. casserole. Combine orange juice, sugar, cornstarch, salt, and orange rind. Pour over carrots. Add butter.
Bake covered for 30 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add raspberries; stir in pineapple with juice.
Pour half of mixture into mold and refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread sour cream on top.
Pour rest of jello on top and set.

title: manhandler soup
directions: Brown ground beef in soup pot along with onion and peppers. Drain.
Add 2 cans of soup and 2 cans of water.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and beans; salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Make syrup with water and sugar; boil 5 minutes, then cool. Add juices to syrup.
Freeze in milk cartons.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Makes about 1 gallon.
Will make about 35 to 40 punch-cup size servings.
Need to take out of freezer about 1 hour before serving.

title: camp fries(chuckwagon grub)
directions: Toss potatoes, onions and seasonings together.
Heat bacon fat in a heavy skillet; add potato mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes.
Cover and cook 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: leeky clam chowder
directions: Brown bacon in large stock pot.
Wash leeks well.
Chop lower part of leeks and add to bacon.
Saute about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add clam, juice and parsley.
Add about 1 pint hot water and heat to boiling.
Add diced potatoes and simmer until tender.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Beat half the cheese with a fork in a small bowl until creamy. Stir in yogurt, garlic, mustard and pepper.
Stir in remaining cheese.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: mushroom and leek quiche
directions: Heat butter and oil; saute leeks over high heat until soft. Stir in flour.
Remove from heat and add mushrooms.
Mix the eggs and add the half and half; mix.
Blend in the leek mixture, cheese and salt and pepper.
Pour the mixture into a prebaked pastry shell, filling to 1/8-inch from top.
Sprinkle top with the oregano and parsley.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add pizza sauce and heat.
Add cooked and drained macaroni with the hamburger mixture. Stir in shredded cheese.

title: peach cobbler
directions: About 2 hours before serving or early in the day:
Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel peaches and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
In large bowl, toss sliced peaches with flour, lemon juice, salt, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon peach mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil; bake 35 to 45 minutes until peach mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, chocolate and milk in a pan and cook until it boils.
Take a cup of cold water and test your chocolate by putting a drop of chocolate in it.
When it forms ball, it's done.

title: pork chop casserole ii
directions: Brown pork chops in hot oil.
Remove chops and add soup to drippings to make gravy.
If gravy is too thick, add milk to thin. Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish with potatoes.
Add green beans.
Place chops on top of beans and cover with gravy.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brownies test done. Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.

title: hot pickle mix
directions: Prepare cucumbers, sweet green and red peppers, carrots, cauliflower and onions. Dissolve salt in 4 quarts water. Pour over vegetables; let stand for 1 hour. With rubber gloves, remove seeds from hot peppers; cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces. Combine remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes. Remove garlic. Drain vegetables. Pack vegetables and peppers (not jalapeno) into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space. Add a piece of jalapeno or red pepper pod to each jar. Pour hot liquid over mix. Adjust caps. Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes about 7 pints.

title: barbecued skillet supper
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add barbecue sauce, water and onion. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms. Continue cooking 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes until top is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix as given in recipe.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Recipe makes 2 pies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Season chicken with seasoned salt or salt and pepper and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix barbecue sauce and Coca-Cola. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn wings over and cook 30 to 35 minutes longer.
(This recipe can be doubled or half of ingredients.)

title: chicken divan bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook spaghetti and drain. In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour until smooth and bubbly. Add chicken broth. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture comes to a full boil (about 5 minutes). Remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and milk. Stir until cheese is melted. In a greased (2-quart) casserole dish, combine spaghetti, chicken, broccoli, mushrooms and cheese mixture. Top with 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Add remaining ingredients, ending with the cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serve over pasta.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in hot water.
Add cold water.
Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add to Jell-O mixture. Mix well and chill until slightly thickened.
Beat and fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Cool until ready to serve.

title: apple saucy goose
directions: Soak goose overnight in salt water.
Place 2 apples in cavity. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes per pound.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine, sugar and salt; blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, stir and add to the mixture.
Add flour and blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Dough must be in a large mixing bowl as it rises slightly. About 3 hours before using rolls, put dough on floured board and knead slightly.
Roll into desired shapes.
(Can roll dough about 1/2 inch thick, cut with a biscuit cutter, butter top with melted butter and fold in half). Put rolls in buttered pan about 1 inch apart and butter tops again.
Allow to rise at room temperature until double in size. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Add beaten egg whites last.
Roll out, cut and fry in deep fat.

title: brown sugar walnut fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk and let come to a rolling boil.
Take from heat. Let cool.
Add the powdered sugar and beat until smooth and thick like fudge.
Add nuts and pour into buttered plate.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Serve warm as a dip with favorite crackers.

title: melissa's apple smiles(her favorite snack!)
directions: Spread 1 side of each apple slice with peanut butter.
Place 3 or 4 tiny marshmallows on top of the peanut butter on one apple slice.
Top with another apple slice, peanut butter side down. Squeeze gently.
Eat right away.
Makes 8 to 10, depending on apple slice thickness.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and cool.
Add pineapple, bananas, marshmallows and 7-Up.
Chill until set.
Easy to serve if made in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add flavoring and blend.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Bake in 2 or 3 loaf pans at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: bean dish
directions: Mix all of the above.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin.
Mix well. Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin mixture.
Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs and add melted butter or margarine.
Firmly pack 2/3 of mixture in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Chill several hours.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 12.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: In casserole dish, layer cream cheese and chili hot beans. Top with shredded cheese.
Cook in microwave on High 3 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Dip with chips.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soak oats in buttermilk (can use sweet milk with the addition of 1 1/2 tablespoons vinegar).
Stir for 1 hour.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir oats mixture.
Add dry ingredients. Fill muffin tins and bake.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: In 10-gallon pot, bring water with all seasonings to a boil. Add crawfish.
Cook for 7 minutes after water reaches 2nd boil. Remove crawfish and dust with additional cayenne pepper and salt. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: gnocchi
directions: Mix together; if dough does not go together, add a little more flour.
Roll dough out in a long round rope about 3/4-inches thick.
Cut each rope into 1/4-inch slices.
Place tines of a fork on top of each slice and quickly pull fork down toward you, flattening Gnocchi into thin oblong shapes.
Repeat with remaining dough.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in big bag or container.
Mix next 3 ingredients in pan and boil for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla after boiling.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn mix and stir.
Divide into 2 pans and bake for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil the rice for 40 minutes.
Boil the shrimp for about 15 minutes.
Take shells off, then slice into small pieces. Stir-fry the pork about 20 minutes.
Put all together in pan and stir.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Brown ribs.
Slice onion and put in crock-pot.
Put browned ribs in pot and add barbecue sauce.
Cook 3 1/2 to 5 hours on high or 7 to 9 hours on low.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chips over low heat and add peanuts.
Stir real good to cover peanuts well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: peanut candy
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and pour onto waxed paper.
When hard, break into pieces.
Use a heavy pan for cooking.
I like this better than peanut brittle.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add jam; mix well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipping cream.
Let stand at least 2 hours.
Beat whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Put in pretty glass bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix in bowl.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Put in well-greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs one at a time. Add alternately sifted dry ingredients with buttermilk. Then add vanilla, nuts, prunes and raisins.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unroll 1 tube crescent rolls and press into pan, stretching dough to cover bottom.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread over dough.
Unroll second tube of crescent rolls and stretch dough over cream cheese layer.
(It's easier to do this in sections!)
Brush top with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet. Sprinkle salt on potatoes.
Sift flour. Cut shortening and potatoes into flour. Add milk gradually, more or less, according to potatoes.
Mix well and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter or shape with hands.
Bake on greased pan for 12 to 15 minutes in preheated oven.
Butter and serve hot.

title: falafel
directions: Soak peas or beans 12 hours in cold water.
Remove skins and place in Cuisinart.
Grind with bread, peppers and parsley.
Add eggs and seasonings.
Let stand 1 hour.
Form into balls and flatten to fry.
Fry in deep oil.
Serve hot with hot salsa to your liking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Before cooking, put topping on top.

title: potato and dumpling soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until done.
Add oleo.
To instructions, mix Bisquick biscuits.
Drop by teaspoon in hot mix. Boil 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple oatmeal
directions: Mix together all ingredients in greased slow cooker. Cook on low 5-6 hours. Serve with ice cream.

title: died and gone to heaven biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add oil.
Sift flour and other ingredients together.
In a large bowl, add liquid.
Stir. Refrigerate. Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 biscuits.
The dough will keep for two weeks in the refrigerator.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green-and-white tuna salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. In a small bowl, whisk together yogurt, mustard and lime juice. Pour over the tuna mixture; toss lightly and serve. Makes 2 servings.

title: nana's brown rice pilaf
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Save 2 tablespoons drippings. Crumble bacon; put aside.
Cook onions and celery in drippings until tender, not brown.
Add broth, uncooked rice, wine, almonds, salt and bacon.
Heat to boiling.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Precook potatoes with jackets; cool and slice in wedges with jackets.
May be refrigerated overnight before sliced.
Combine bacon, mayo and cheese.
Spread over potatoes and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli in water until tender.
Mix broccoli with salt, pepper, milk, margarine, chicken bouillon and cheese, stirring constantly over medium heat until cheese melts.
Mix flour and water until flour is completely dissolved.
Pour into soup mixture.
Stir constantly over medium heat until soup gets slightly thickened.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg; beat well. Add sifted ingredients; mix well.
Roll in small balls; dip into sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rices as per instructions on bag or box.
In meantime heat 2 tablespoons of oil in large frypan.
Saute onion and garlic until golden.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add cubed meats and fry until browned.
Return onion to pan.
Add cooked rice and the rest of the ingredients, except 1 can consomme.
Stir mixture well and put into greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Heat other can of consomme and stir into mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Sprinkle the slivered almonds on for last 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes with 1 stick margarine, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, marshmallows, brown sugar and white sugar in a saucepan. Stir until marshmallows melt.
Place mixture into casserole dish. Combine 1/2 stick melted margarine, frosted flakes and pecans. Place on top of potato mixture.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Beat egg yolks with beater and add dry ingredients, beating well.
Slowly add milk; cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir well and pour into a cool, baked crust.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared pans. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Drizzle with Caramel Glaze.

title: mustard greens with slab bacon
directions: Rinse bacon and place in heavy pot with about 3 quarts of water.
Sprinkle with crushed red pepper and cook with lid on for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Stir in flour, then chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto cookie or baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fantasy freeze pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and pour into crust.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with additional whipped topping and berries.

title: queso ole
directions: Cook macaroni dinner as directions call for.
After you drain the macaroni, add the cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and stir lightly. Brown the ground meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer the macaroni, then the meat on top.
Cook at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When serving, top with sour cream and tomatoes, with tortilla chips on the side.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in salad oil until crumbly.
Add onions, celery, soups, bean sprouts and 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Stir in rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Turn into greased casserole; cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Top with noodles and bake 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cobbler pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and sugar. Mix in milk with spoon. Spread over pie by dropping by spoonfuls.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. In a separate bowl, mix together the milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Combine together and mix well.
Layer the crushed cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon creamy mixture in pan; spread evenly. Add another layer of crushed cookies.
Refrigerate overnight. Top off with plastic flowers or gummy worms for a special look.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets. Add enough water to beet juice to measure 1 1/2 cups liquid. Bring liquid to a boil. Add Jell-O. Stir well to dissolve. Add sugar, vinegar and horseradish. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add beets. Chill until Jell-O is set.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain juice from salmon and set aside.
Mix drained salmon with 1 egg.
Add flour.
Stir in flour with fork.
The mixture will be real thick.
Take 1/4 cup salmon juice and add 1 heaping teaspoonful of baking powder to the juice; beat with a fork. Mixture will foam.
Pour this into your salmon mixture and mix again with fork.
Use 2 ice tea spoons and scoop up half spoonful into deep fryer half full of hot oil.
Tidbits will float on top of hot oil and turn themselves as they cook.
They will be done in a few seconds.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef and add chili powder.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, eggs and half the grated cheese.
Add this to the beef.
Separate biscuits (pull apart to make 2 pieces).
Press into bottom of 8-inch square dish.
Add meat mixture and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together for approximately two minutes. Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° approximately
20 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: diet "blocks"
directions: Combine and heat, stirring until dissolved.
Pour into a pan and chill until firm.
Cut into "blocks."

title: chellah(jewish sabbath bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast	in water; add sugar, salt, oil and egg; stir. Add flour,	half
at
a time (may not need all).
Knead until smooth
and
elastic.
Let	rise
until
doubled.
Punch down, divide
in	half;
divide
each half into quarters.
For each loaf, divide
one quarter
into
3	pieces.
Take 3 large pieces, roll
into	long
"snakes."
Braid.
Take
smaller pieces, repeat process.
Put small braid on top of large braid and tuck ends
under.
Repeat for second loaf.
Let rise until doubled (or almost);
oil
lightly
to	keep from drying out. Glaze with beaten
egg
yolk
and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, 350° for 40 minutes.
Best eaten warm and broken off loaf with fingers and buttered.

title: country ham 'n red-eye gravy
directions: Soak ham in cold water and sugar for at least 1/2 hour.
Wash well and dry.
Fry in oil until brown.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: honey-ginger chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken, in a small bowl. Place chicken on unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat, about 8 minutes, or until chicken is tender, turning once.
Brush often with honey mixture during broiling. Serve with rice and asparagus, if desired.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix and water, stirring with a fork until blended.
Press mixture in bottom of a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Cook ground beef, green peppers and onions in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and spoon over crust.

title: party spread
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: In skillet, heat oil and brown meat; drain. Combine 1 1/2 cups water, soup and meat; bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Stir in green peppers, soy sauce, ginger and garlic; simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until meat is tender. Add cornstarch blended with remaining water. Bring to a boil, then simmer until thick, about 5 minutes. Stir constantly. Serve over rice.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; beat in eggs, milk and melted shortening.
Pour into large cake pan and over top; put 1/4 cup butter, 1 cup brown sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together.
Sprinkle with chopped nutmeats.
Pecans are especially nice.
One-half of recipe makes a small cake.

title: sweet potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and slice each potato into 1/4-inch thick ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into wedges. In a gallon size plastic bag or large bowl, combine potatoes, egg whites and cinnamon.
Pour potatoes onto well-greased baking sheet and spread out in a single layer, leaving a small space between. Place on bottom rack of oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the wedges are crispy.
Turn once.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beefy jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine 1 cup meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, oil and corn in bowl; mix and set aside.
Saute ground beef until lightly browned. Drain and set aside.
Sprinkle remaining meal in a greased 10 1/2-inch skillet.
Pour half of meal batter into skillet. Sprinkle evenly with beef.
Top with onions and cheese.
Add peppers on top.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: double peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until chocolate melts.
Stir until well blended.
Add peanuts and stir until peanuts are coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill.
Yields about 2 dozen clusters.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Have butcher cut pockets for stuffing in 6 double loin pork chops.
Take a sharp knife and deepen and widen these pockets yourself, being careful not to cut through the top or bottom of the chop.
Season inside and out with salt and freshly ground black pepper and stuff to capacity with the following dressing.

title: cape cod fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add potatoes, carrot, seasonings, milk and water.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add fish; simmer about 15 minutes more.
Stir in corn with liquid (Niblets are okay). Warm through.
Serve with a sprinkle of parsley.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat and onions, then add all ingredients except beans. Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours, then add beans and cook 15 minutes more.

title: spiced cider punch
directions: Combine water and sugar to spices in saucepan.
Stir over heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add cider with lemon juice.
Chill. Add club soda.
Pour over blocks of ice in small punch bowl. Garnish with lemon slices.
Yields 20 punch cup servings.

title: spicy kielbasa
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces. Place in crock-pot with remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 6 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line pie shell with cream cheese.
Boil sugar, water and cornstarch.
Add jello; cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Put in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Drain.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with potatoes, carrots, peas, celery, onion and rice.

title: life-like cookie dough
directions: Cream (butter) shortening and sugar; beat in the egg.
Add milk in which soda has been dissolved, vanilla, flour and salt. Chill.
Roll to 1/8 of an inch thickness.
Dip cutter in flour before cutting out cookies.

title: mocha upside-down cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Melt together the unsweetened chocolate and 1 tablespoon of butter in double boiler and add to first mixture.
Mix and blend well.
Mix the milk and vanilla.
Combine and add to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: chicken cantaloupe ring
directions: Toss chicken, celery, grapes, lemon juice and seasonings together.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut slices across whole cantaloupe.
Remove seeds and peel slices.
Place each slice on lettuce leaf on salad plate.
Fill hole in center with chicken salad.
Garnish with almonds.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Mix and cool the boiling water and lemon jello.
Mix in another bowl the cake mix, oil, lemon extract and eggs.
Combine both mixtures.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: virginia's lemon ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in sugar, lemon, evaporated milk and salt. Pour in homogenized milk to fill line and freeze.

title: southern instant tea
directions: Mix all together and store in tightly covered jar.
To make, use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
Drink hot or iced.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and cool (microwave or double boiler). Sift together dry ingredients. Stir softened butter. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla. Mix to dampen flour. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed by mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand. Add eggs, yolk and chocolate. Beat 1 minute. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° about 65 minutes. Cool and glaze.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend with fork. Roll out half on floured surface. Makes 2 shells.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla all together.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Add nuts; stir well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased pan or ungreased nonstick pan.

title: tuna salad
directions: Be sure to blend cottage cheese in blender until creamy.
Pour creamy cottage cheese into another bowl.
Add vanilla supplement and hand blend.
Drain tuna well and add to creamy mixture.
If you like your tuna spicy, you may add chopped onion and celery or other items that are "legal" on the program.
Chill.
Can be used for a couple of days.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in shortening until brown.
Add onion, pepper, celery, tomato and sugar.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in meat and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until heated.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve green peppers lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash.
Drop in boiling salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain and put in baking pan. Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Spoon into pepper halves and top each half with cheese. Cover and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: yankee potato nachos(microwave)
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 9-inch plate, overlapping slices. Loosely cover and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until tender. Spread salsa over potatoes.
Place green pepper and chili peppers on top of salsa.
Top with cheese and microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cook squash on medium heat until you can put a fork in them. Lift out of water and cut in half lengthwise.
Scrape out each half with spoon and reserve in a large bowl to be mixed with more ingredients.
Place squash hulls in shallow baking dish.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Drain fruit.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon together.
Take juice from fruit to mix dry ingredients.
Pour butter into 2-quart casserole.
Pour fruit in with butter.
Pour mix over fruit and butter (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture until ball forms.
Divide in half.
(May freeze.)
Press into pizza pan.
Prick with fork. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: eva's irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and optional caraway seed and raisins.
Mix well.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs. Add buttermilk and butter.

Combine well. Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients, stirring with wooden spoon just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn out dough onto lightly floured board. Knead lightly until smooth, about 1 minute. Shape dough into a ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
With hands, flatten into a 7-inch circle. With a sharp knife, cutting 1/4-inch deep, mark top into quarters.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and loaf sounds hollow when rapped with knuckle. Remove loaf to wire rack.
Brush top with butter and cool completely.

title: mexican lasagne(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, garlic and peppers.
Cook, stirring until soft (5 minutes).
Add soup, enchilada sauce, chicken, chili powder and cumin.
Bring to a simmer.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Cook sugar and water slowly for 10 minutes.
Add grated rind to syrup and continue cooking for several minutes.
Strain.
Add syrup to fruit juices.
Cool.
Pour into tray and allow to freeze firm. Remove mixture to ice cold mixing bowl.
Beat with rotary eggbeater until light.
Add coffee cream and fold in between egg whites to which a pinch of salt has been added.
Pour into tray and freeze. Makes 8 servings.

title: applesauce christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Combine applesauce and soda; beat in.
Combine rest of dry ingredients and add.
Stir in molasses, vanilla, raisins and pecans.

title: red lion salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour in jar and mix well or blend slowly.

title: instant cherry cream pie
directions: Cream cheese until softened. Add 1/2 cup of the milk, a little at a time, blending until mixture is very smooth. Add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding. Beat with mixer just until well mixed. Pour into crust. Chill until set. Drain cherries, reserving syrup. Add sugar and cornstarch to syrup. Stir until smooth. Cook until thickened. Add cherries. Cool slightly. Spoon over cream filling. Chill.

title: pineapple surprise salad
directions: Boil the can of crushed pineapple (juice and all) with 1/3 cup sugar until sugar is well dissolved.
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup water.
Add pineapple mixture; let stand in refrigerator until mixture is almost jelled.
Add Cheddar cheese, Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Stir until well blended.
Let jell overnight before serving.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Slice cookie dough; cut slices into quarters.
Place each portion in miniature muffin cup.
Bake, using package directions. Place 1 miniature peanut butter cup in each cookie.
Cool in muffin cups.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: bouillabaisse(low-fat seafood soup)
directions: Cook the onions slowly in the olive oil for about 5 minutes. Do not brown.
Stir in the tomatoes and garlic and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the water, herbs, seasoning and clam juice to the kettle with onions.
Bring to boil and cook at a very slow boil for 30 minutes.
You can prepare this far and refrigerate.

title: pizza bubbles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a round cake pan, be sure it covers the bottom.
Mix together tomato sauce, oil, basil, oregano, garlic and onion.
Separate 1 can biscuits, cut each into 4 pieces.
Toss pieces into sauce and place in buttered pan.
Pour any remaining sauce over and cover top with 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Drain all fruit well and place in Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup light brown sugar on fruit and scatter small chunks of butter over fruit. Sprinkle cinnamon and/or nutmeg.
Heat 25 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 12.
(Great side dish for ham or turkey.)

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add oil, pineapple juice and eggs.
Stir in coconut, zucchini and nuts.
Place in greased pan. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting as desired.

title: crab and brie stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush a large baking dish with olive oil.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Clean caps.
Season with salt and pepper.
Separate crab into 1/2-inch morsels, discarding any cartilage.
Cut Brie into 1/2-inch pieces.
