Fill each mushroom cap halfway with crab; top with a piece of Brie.
Place on greased baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.
Yields 10 to 12.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook shortening, flour, chili powder and salt together.
Then add enough water to make it as thick as beef gravy; cook slowly and well.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and some red peppers.
Simmer together for about 10 minutes.
Add hot sauce to the other sauce and cook tortillas in this for about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: italian parmesan twists
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In 9-inch pie pan, combine Parmesan cheese and
Italian seasonings.
Divide dough into 8 sections; divide each section into 4 pieces.
(There should be 32 pieces of dough.) Roll
each piece into 4-inch ropes.
Dip each rope in butter
and roll in Parmesan mixture.	Twist rope 3 times. Place on greased cookie
sheets.
Bake
for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Boil blackberries, sugar and water; reduce heat to medium. After mixing biscuit dough, drop by spoonfuls into boiling mixture. Cook until dough is done, approximate time 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine ingredients.
If you like, you may add chopped water chestnuts, drained.
Mix well.
Nabisco bacon thins really set this off.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup into baking dish.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake about 20 minutes at 375° or until they are heated through.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix together.
Line 3 large or 6 small pans with foil.
Pack pans full.
Bake at 225° for 2 1/2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: candy balls
directions: Melt caramels and milk until smooth.
Blend together dry ingredients.
Pour the caramel mixture over this.
Make into balls with moistened hands as they are a little sticky.

title: strawberry-orange frost
directions: Place strawberries and orange juice in blender.
Cover and blend on a medium speed until just blended.
Add 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream and blend on a low speed a few seconds.
Pour into glasses.

title: sunday crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, set aside.
Beat the eggs, sugar, salt, milk and margarine while still warm.
Slowly add the yeast and flour.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Roll each into a circle about 1/4-inch thick. Using a pizza cutter, cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll each wedge, starting at the large end.
Place on a greased pan and let rise 2 or 2 1/2 hours until double.
Bake at 325° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: quick beet borscht
directions: Heat beef broth, if using a bouillon cube add
10 1/2-ounces water, beets with liquid, cabbage, sugar, and onion to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer gently five minutes.
Stir in lemon juice. Chill thoroughly.
Top each serving with a spoon of sour cream. Serve with Ritz crackers.
This borscht can also be served hot.

title: addie hall's applesauce cake
directions: Cream well butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Mix flour mixture alternately with applesauce to the egg mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Put soda in a measuring cup.
Pour 1/2 cup hot water over it and add to the batter.
Stir well.
Add raisins, dates and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Pour dressing over the first 4 ingredients that have been layered.
Put in refrigerator overnight or for 12 hours.

title: oven baked halibut steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut steak crosswise in half.
Chop bread into small pieces.
On waxed paper mix bread, parsley, salt and pepper.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish arrange steaks; press bread crumb mixture on top.
Bake, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: party pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Heat pecans in 250° oven in shallow pan; pour heated pecans in large bowl.
Drizzle mixture over nuts; stir well.
Return to oven; toast 1 hour at 250°.
Rice and Corn Chex may be substituted for some pecans.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions, using milk and pineapple juice as cooking liquids.
Cool.
Save 1 tablespoon of raisins for garnish.
Stir remaining raisins and 3/4 carton Cool Whip into pudding.
Measure and drain 1/2 cup pineapple for garnish.

title: savory sauce
directions: Simmer 5 minutes.
This gives a "lift" to ordinary hamburger when using it as an entree.
Serve sauce on top of hamburger steak.

title: white party icing
directions: Combine powdered sugar, Crisco, hot water and flavoring.
Beat on highest speed of mixer until well blended and of spreading consistency.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Cook about 15 minutes.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Good as appetizer.

title: lasagna "al forno"
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in oil. Drain well.
Add sauce. Simmer 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Layer in oblong baking dish the sauce, lasagna, cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers. Top with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: skillet lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together in large skillet.
Spread noodles over the meat.
Spread cottage cheese on noodles.
Mix tomato juice, oregano, basil, salt and garlic salt together; pour over cottage cheese.
Do not stir.
Put lid on and cook on low heat until noodles are done, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on and melt.

title: herb bread
directions: Slice loaf of French bread and put mixture between slices and wrap loaf in foil.
Place in a warm oven for about 20 minutes.
Or spread mixture on barbecue or loaf bread and toast under broiler. Great with steaks, spaghetti or any meats.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sue's potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients, except oleo and potatoes.
Mix and mix and mix.
Add hash browns.
Mix.
Cut up oleo in small chunks.
Press into mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice dressing
directions: Put giblets in little cooking oil and fry for a little time. In another pan, make a little roux with flour, then put all together and boil a long time with green onions.
When cooked tender, put cooked rice in and stir good.
Season to taste, and it's ready to serve.

title: microwave bubble ring
directions: Mix butter, water, brown sugar and nuts.
Dip rolls of refrigerator dough into mixture and place in around glass pan. Push center aside and insert a glass or muffin pan or custard cup. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn upside-down onto plate.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar; cream together.
Add Wesson oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add grated apples and chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a boiler and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and spoon onto wax paper.
Let totally cool.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
In saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and defatted chicken broth.
Mix cornstarch with water until smooth and add to sauce mixture.
Cook sauce until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks to sauce and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover. Add green pepper strips and baste with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Cut ice cream into 1/2-inch slices and arrange on bottom and sides of a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let ice cream soften slightly; then smooth slices together with a spoon, forming a pie shell.
Freeze 2 1/2 hours or until firm.
Combine 1 egg and 2 egg yolks in a small, heavy saucepan.
Beat well.
Stir in sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Fold mixture into whipped cream. Beat 2 egg whites until stiff; fold into lemon mixture.
Spoon filling into ice cream shell.
Freeze until firm (about 5 hours). Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before slicing.
Garnish with grated lemon rind and mint leaves, if desired.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Sprinkle undissolved jello over the cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with fruit comparable to the flavor of jello you use.
(Example, strawberries on strawberry jello.) Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours and serve in a large bowl.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Melt butter and brown onion.
Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, butter, onions, salt and pepper.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put grated cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water, butter and salt to rolling boil.
Reduce heat; stir in flour, mixing vigorously, until mixture leaves sides of pan in ball.
Remove from heat.
Place flour mixture in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 30 seconds after each one.

title: t-bone specialty
directions: Marinate steak in Italian dressing overnight in refrigerator (or longer).
Bake in 325° oven, basting with Italian dressing until done to your taste.
Serve with baked potato green salad and corn-on-the-cob and rolls.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until done.
Drain and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour can of celery soup (diluted with milk) over cabbage. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread cheese and margarine over cabbage mixture.
Mash crackers and put on top of all.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, coconut, pecans, graham cracker crumbs and egg whites in a large bowl and mix well (do not beat).
Turn into pie shell.
Bake until filling is set, about 35 minutes.
(Do not overbake!) Garnish as desired.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade and milk.
Stir and mix Cool Whip into it. Stir real good.
Put into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: country brown bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins, add butter, sugar and egg to water and raisins.
Mix.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Blend all ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and mix.
Grease and flour three No. 2 tin pans.
Spoon batter into pans filling each 1/2 full. Bake in preheated oven at 250° until dark brown.
Insert knife into middle, when it comes out clean, bread is done.
Approximately 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer tea, cinnamon and cloves in 1 quart water.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water, then add 3 quarts cold water to make 3/4 gallon.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Remove cinnamon sticks, cloves and tea bags and add to juices.
Mix all ingredients and serve hot or cold.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice or pasta.

title: some more casserole
directions: Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in 1/2 cup of Minute rice or 1 cup cooked rice.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with chow mein noodles and bake 30 minutes more.

title: mom's old fashioned sugar cakes
directions: Beat margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and sugar; beat well after addition.
Add 1/3 of flour to mixture; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup of buttermilk and mix well.
Add 1/2 of remaining flour, remaining buttermilk and remainder of flour, mixing well after each addition.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, 2 to 3-inches apart. Sprinkle cookies with sugar and top with 2 raisins.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
I like to start them on low level about 5 to 6 minutes, and then move them to higher level for rest of baking time.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and wipe mushrooms with paper towel and place in a glass bowl.
Combine olive oil, garlic and parsley and pour over mushrooms.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 48 hours (in the same bowl), stirring occasionally.
Add salt when marinated.
Put in a covered jar.
The mushrooms will keep for about 2 weeks.

title: sauce fettucine alfredo
directions: Heat butter and cream in saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over 12 ounces cooked fettuccine.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring (optional).
Pour into crust. Bake 8 minutes.
Cool. Chill thoroughly. Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 1 pie.

title: special peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to the soft ball stage.
Add raw peanuts; stir all the time until the peanuts pop and mixture is golden brown.
Remove from heat; stir in salt, soda and paraffin and quickly pour thin on buttered cookie sheet.
Break into squares just before candy is cold.

title: ribbon salad(dietetic)
directions: Prepare first box of jello and pour into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Beat cottage cheese in blender until smooth and creamy.
Drain pineapple.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Heat remaining juice and mix into softened gelatin.
Combine juice-gelatin mixture with cottage cheese.
Add Equal, vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Mix thoroughly and pour on top of set jello. Refrigerate until set.
Prepare second box of jello and pour over cottage cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Yield: 9 servings. Exchanges: 1 serving = 1 fruit, 1 lean meat and 115 calories.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Boil water, sugar and jello together for 5 minutes. Puree thawed strawberries in the blender. Add strawberries, pineapple juice and Sprite to cooled jello mixture.

title: salsa
directions: Process the first 4 ingredients in food processor, then add together the rest of the ingredients.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs together, press in bottom of pan.
Beat sugar, eggs and 1 stick of margarine until fluffy.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas on top.
Add pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate until served.

title: paul's pound cake
directions: Early in the day, set out eggs, margarine and cream cheese to reach room temperature.
When ready to cook cake, combine margarine, cream cheese and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Cream well.
Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add cake flour.
Cook in tube or Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300° or until done.

title: sausage
directions: Mix well in a bowl and refrigerate.
Take out once a day for 3 days.
Mix well on fourth day.
Form rolls (we make 6 rolls about the size of a Ritz cracker).
Place on top rack of the oven and bake for 8 hours at 150°.
I double recipe.

title: aunt dora's salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows, lemon jello and cream cheese. Take off stove and add pineapple, nuts and cherries. Cool and stir in whipping cream and chill. Pour on strawberry jello after making by package directions.

title: fruit salad
directions: Reserve juice from peaches and pineapple.
Using reserved juice, add 1 small box instant pudding and 3 tablespoons of powdered orange juice, such as Tang.

title: elegant fudge frosting(servings:  4)
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a heavy saucepan. Place over low heat and allow to come to a rolling boil.
Boil exactly 1 minute.
Cool mixture to room temperature before beating.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth and the right consistency to spread on cake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cool. Grind cranberries and oranges in food processor.
Add along with nuts to cooled jello mixture and chill in covered container until firm.

title: cut-out gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Stir in egg and molasses and beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients and mix into molasses mixture.

title: tortilla soup(4 servings)
directions: In a large heavy pot, heat the oil over moderately high heat. Add half the tortilla strips and cook, stirring, until pale golden, about 1 minute. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Repeat with the remaining tortilla strips. Reduce the heat to moderately low. Add the onion, garlic and spices; cook, stirring, for 5 minutes. Add the broth, tomatoes, bay leaves, salt, cilantro leaves, if using, and 1/3 of the tortilla strips. Bring to a simmer. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Remove the
bay leaves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator.

title: easy cookies from cake mix
directions: Mix well and using a teaspoon, drop spoonfuls of batter on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Transfer sausage to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In the sausage drippings, saute celery, onions and peppers until lightly browned.
Transfer to casserole.
To casserole, add water chestnuts, rice, soup, water and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.

title: prune pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and prunes.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and flour and add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use a medium casserole dish, line bottom and sides with vanilla wafers.
Fix pudding according to box directions.
Slice 1 1/2 bananas over vanilla wafers, then pour pudding over bananas enough to cover the bananas.
Put another layer of vanilla wafers, bananas, then pudding on top. Continue until all vanilla wafers and bananas are gone.
Separate eggs and use whites.
Whip whites and sugar to make meringue. Spread on top of pudding, then bake for 15 minutes or until meringue is lightly brown.

title: ginger candied carrots
directions: Place carrot pieces in a saucepan and add cold water to cover.
Cook carrots until tender, 25-30 minutes.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add brown sugar, ginger and caraway seeds.
Mix and set aside.
When carrots are done, drain and return to the pot.
Pour butter mixture over them and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to dish and serve immediately.
6 portions.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn and nuts (which have been dumped in large greased pan).
Stir with wooden spoon.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange breasts in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Pour rice over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Add salt and pepper and drop 1/2 to 1 stick butter on top of mixture.
Bake, covered, 2 hours and another 1/2 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: sweet dills
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, water and salt for 5 minutes.
Pour into jars filled with small cucumbers and dill.
Set in hot water in a kettle or canner.
Boil for a few minutes.
Seal.
Let stand until cold or overnight.
Makes 7 quarts.
Half bushel of small cucumbers makes 22 to 23 quarts.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line a greased 9 x 13 pan with quartered tortillas.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour on top of tortillas. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: rice pudding
directions: Grease baking dish.
Wash rice.
Add milk, cinnamon or nutmeg, sugar and salt.
Bake in 275° oven for 3 hours.
Stir frequently during first hour.
Add raisins or eggs during last 1/2 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together. Place on waxed paper and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place chopped walnuts (enough to cover outside of ball) on waxed paper. Roll the ball around on nuts till ball is covered.
For decoration place a marachino cherry on top. Enjoy!

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites real stiff, gradually.
Add sugar, beating constantly.
Add dash of salt.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet(s).
Place in oven preheated to 350°.
Turn off oven immediately.
Leave overnight.

title: stromboli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thaw bread and let rise.
Roll out bread to make a long narrow strip about 6 inches wide.
Spread pizza sauce all over one side of dough.
Heap all of the ingredients down the middle of the dough, putting the cheese on top.
Fold sides of dough around and tuck to make a roll.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake until bread is lightly brown, about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Take first 5 ingredients and cook in saucepan until thick and cool.
Add lemon juice, sour cream and lemon rind.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: never fail fudge(my grandmother's recipe)
directions: Mix milk, marshmallow, sugar, salt and butter in a saucepan, stirring constantly; heat to boiling and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan and cool until firm.
Press whole nuts into top of fudge for decoration before fudge hardens.
Makes about 2 pounds of creamy fudge.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush up cookies.
Save 1 cup.
Pour rest in bottom of pan evenly.
Soften cream cheese; then add confectioners sugar and Cool Whip in one bowl; set aside.

title: grandma bonnie taunton's peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients, except soda, until temperature reaches 300° on candy thermometer or the peanuts pop in the pan.
Stir in soda and pour on a flat buttered pan.
Allow to cool completely. Break into small pieces.

title: cubed steak casserole
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown slightly.
Place steak in bottom of casserole bowl.
Add sliced onion, then potatoes.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix altogether; heat in crock-pot on high 2 hours, then to low.
Ready to serve.

title: punch for 100
directions: Mix together Jello, 4 cups water and sugar; boil for 3 minutes.
Add frozen juices and pineapple juice; stir together. Just before serving add water, ginger ale and ice.

title: green and gold casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shred
squash.
Drain
well
any excess water.
Chop onion and saute
in oil.
To the onion add oregano, parsley, salt, eggs and
milk.
In	a
greased casserole, spread a layer of the shredded squash.
Top with a layer of crushed saltines and then with
one cup of the cheese.
Put the remainder of saltines and cheese
over
all
and
pour the mixture
of onion, oregano,
salt,
parsley,
eggs
and
milk. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Prepare icing.
Spread over cake.

title: chicken shell salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions on the package and drain. Combine shells, chicken, celery, radishes, green pepper and onion. Blend Blue cheese dressing, sour cream, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Stir dressing into salad mixture.
Cover and chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole and cover with soups (do not dilute).
Add onion and green pepper. Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: caramel apple custard
directions: Combine pie filling and brown sugar.
Divide evenly between 8 custard cups or use a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add salt and sugar to beaten eggs.
Slowly stir in milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups or baking dish, pouring into a spoon over the apple mixture to avoid mixing.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix sour cream with soup.
Spread a single layer of dried beef on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cut chicken into strips or bite size pieces and put on beef.
Evenly distribute mushrooms over chicken.
Spread the sour cream mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes and serve over hot noodles.

title: party mix
directions: Roast for 2 hours at 250° the dry ingredients.
Boil butter and oil with spices and pour over dry stuff.
Stir often as it cooks.

title: zucchini and gravy
directions: Peel and chop zucchini into small pieces.
In saucepan, saute zucchini in oil with garlic and onions.
When soft, add tomato sauce.
Simmer for approximately 20 minutes or until zucchini is completely cooked.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Sprinkle with Locatelli cheese and cook about 10 minutes, until eggs are completely cooked.
Serve as a side dish.

title: manicotti
directions: In a larger saucepan, brown sausage and drain.
Remove 1/2 of sausage and set aside.
Stir tomato paste, sauce, water and brown sugar into sausage and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients, sausage, Ricotta cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella, egg and parsley.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and preheat oven to 350°. Boil sliced cabbage just until tender.
Drain.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients by hand.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and chopped nuts.
Mix and bake one hour in preheated oven at 350° or until toothpick comes out dry.
Remove from oven and while still warm (hot) pour over the top the juice from lemon mixed with 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand until cold and remove from pan. (This bread is a sweet tea type bread, is simple to make as all mixing is done by hand.
Bread freezes well.)

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May top with frosting or chocolate bar.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain baked beans.
Mix all ingredients in large skillet or crock-pot.
Cook together until onion is done.
Very easy, very good.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper; form into patties and put in a skillet.
Combine water and soup; pour over patties.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes. Delicious!

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and dissolve cream cheese in it.
Stir until smooth. Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water and dissolve in soup mixture. Cool 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and put in a mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold to serve.
Serve with party rye.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach well and break into large bite-size pieces.
Add onion, eggs, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble on top just before serving.

title: one bowl coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: campfire supper
directions: Slice onion, carrots and potatoes.
Make hamburger into patties.
Place hamburger onto aluminum foil and add onion slice, carrot slices and potato slices.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt. Wrap aluminum foil tightly.
Then use another piece and wrap in the other direction.
Place on wire rack of grill or open campfire over hot coals.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes, until done. Turn every 5 to 10 minutes to bake well.
This can be done individually or as a group dish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pudding as directed and cool.
After cake is cool, cut into small pieces. Layer all the ingredients in a punch bowl in the following order: pieces of cake, pudding, pineapple, strawberries, blueberries and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and garnish with strawberries.

title: berry banana smoothie
directions: Freeze cut up banana in a plastic bag, then use pieces straight from freezer.
In a blender container, combine the frozen banana pieces, desired berries, orange juice and yogurt.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, vanilla, sour cream, eggs, rum flavoring and oil in a large mixing bowl. Beat 3 minutes on medium speed. Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Beat 2 minutes longer. Fold in remaining chips and pecans. Batter will be very stiff. Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 30 minutes on wire rack before removing from pan. Turn out and cool completely. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cut peaches in bite size.
Place in bottom of cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over top of peaches.
Cut butter into squares. Place on top of entire cake mix.
Cook at 350° until top is brown.

title: sausage pasties
directions: Crumble 1/2 butter.
Add flour, salt and water.
Mix to stiff dough.
Roll out; dot with remaining butter.
Fold.
Roll out once.
Use with meat filling.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, egg yolk and peppermint extract.
Beat at medium speed, until mixture is light and fluffy (2 to 3 minutes).
Continue beating, gradually adding flour and cocoa, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Shape dough into candy canes; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 7 minutes, or until set.
Cool completely. Decorate with Peppermint Icing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, cinnamon and butter together.
Place apples in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put mixture over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion and drain. Boil until done.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in casserole.
Lay slices of cheese on top.
Pour soup and wine combined over top of chicken.
Sprinkle crushed dressing mix on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime slush punch
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Cover and freeze for 8 hours.
Take out 1 hour before using.
Add ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chili
directions: Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
The secret is to cook the day before, refrigerate and heat again.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Mix peas, beans, corn, pimentos and salt together.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, water and paprika; mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquid over vegetables.
Chill 24 hours.
Keeps well.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: Clean spinach and break into easy bite sizes.
Make sure spinach is completely dry before tossing.
In a large bowl toss spinach with sliced mushrooms, chopped onion, grated carrots and crumbled bacon.
Put into serving bowl and place egg quarters on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and cover.
Run on blend for 20 seconds or until smooth.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade and sweetened milk concentrate in medium bowl until just blended. Whisk in food coloring.
Mix well. Fold in dessert topping.
Turn mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
To serve, garnish with additional whipped topping and chocolate curls or lime slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stirred fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs and add flour and spices.
Add fruit, nuts and raisins to mixture.
Cook at 350° in two long greased pans for 15 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Repeat process 2 more times.
Pack in large tube pan lined with greased brown paper. Return to oven and cook 15 minutes.
Total Cooking Time:
1 hour. Let stand 15 minutes and remove.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough for short time.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Great cookies!!!

title: apple crunch
directions: Fill bottom of pan with pie filling. Chop nuts and put in with dry cake mix.
Place dry mixture on top of pie filling.
Melt butter and pour on cake mix.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: squash puppies
directions: Beat egg; add buttermilk, onion and squash.
Combine cornmeal and flour.
Add to squash mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot fryer of cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl mix corn muffin mix, eggs, cottage cheese, salt and thawed broccoli.
Add melted margarine, then add milk and pour into the 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 425° about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Freezes well.

title: rum slush
directions: Freeze, stirring once every 8 hours.
Serve in a glass 3/4 full; add 7-Up.

title: english tea cookies
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Add margarine.
Cut mixture until it looks like coarse meal.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Dust with confectioners sugar; put a raisin on top of each one.
Bake for 9 minutes at 375°, or until edges are lightly browned.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple until it starts to bubble and stir in jello. Then add buttermilk.
Let it start to set, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash until smooth.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refill the whites and garnish with paprika or parsley.
Serves 4.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato. When done, mash real fine.
Let cool, then add vanilla. Start adding sugar until it forms a ball.
Roll out on sugar-covered surface, then cover good with peanut butter. Roll it up into a roll and cut into sections. Cool in refrigerator.

title: fresh fruit tart
directions: Bake cookie crust; cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on low speed until smooth.
Beat in whipping cream on low speed until blended; beat on medium speed until stiff peaks form. Spread over crust to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Arrange fruit in circles on crust.
Heat jelly over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Brush over fruit.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: *If toasted coconut is not available, use vanilla instant pudding mix with 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.

title: french beef oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients in a heavy 3-quart ovenproof pan.
Cover and bake, stirring 3 times, in three hours until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
Discard bay leaves before serving.
Add 2 cups frozen peas.

title: venison shish-ka-bobs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except venison.
Place venison cubes in marinade for 2 hours.
Remove venison from marinade. Place on skewers and wrap with bacon.
Place skewers on grill until venison is thoroughly cooked.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375°
for 7 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, Cool Whip and pecans.
Put on cooled crust.
Chill. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir until well dissolved.
Add frozen raspberries (don't thaw).
Let stand until syrupy.
Pour over cream cheese and chill.
May add 4 ounces Cool Whip and chopped nuts at serving time (optional).

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust. Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add 1/2 cup cold water. Refrigerate until it starts to set, then add fruit (1 pint crushed strawberries).
If using lime jello, add 1 large can crushed pineapple, drained.
Spread over cream layer and refrigerate.

title: cook it til they're starving venison
directions: Flour heavily seasoned venison steaks with your favorite seasoning mix (Season All, Greek seasoning, Cajun, salt and pepper, garlic, etc.)

title: congealed slaw salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix mayonnaise and cold water, vinegar and salt; add jello.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until fluffy; add cabbage, celery and onion.
Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce.
May add 2 tablespoons hot horseradish for variety.
Green pepper and diced cucumber may be added also. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: nut butter ball
directions: Cream the butter until soft and smooth, then blend in extract. Mix flour, salt and nuts.
Add and mix well.
(This is easier if kneaded in with the hands.)
Refrigerate 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, tiny fingers or crescents. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
While cookies are still warm, coat with powdered sugar.
Re-roll them after they are cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° oven.
Into large bowl, sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add sugars, egg, vanilla and butter.
With wooden spoon, beat until smooth and well combined, about 1 minute. Stir in walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by the tablespoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Remove to wire rack; cool.

title: veal piccata
directions: Dip veal into egg, then into flour to coat.
Brown in oil in skillet; remove and keep warm.
Add broth to pan juices, stirring to blend in meat particles.
Combine cornstarch and wine and stir into broth with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over veal and garnish with lemon slices.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large 9-inch DEEP DISH, buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
This recipe will make its own crust.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Place chicken first, celery stalk, parsley, lemon slices, diced onion, celery seed, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Cover in water and cook, covered, about 18 minutes, depending on size of chicken breasts.
When chicken is done, drain and discard other ingredients.
Cut chicken in long slices or dice (large).
Place green onion, other celery stalk and paprika.

title: enola's barbecued shrimp
directions: In a large skillet over high heat, melt the margarine.
Add the shrimp, basil, salt, oregano, white and red peppers and file powder.

Saute for 3 minutes or until the shrimp start to stick to the bottom of the skillet, but stir constantly to prevent burning. Add the remaining ingredients; cook, stirring for 5 minutes or until the sauce thickens.
Serve hot.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add water gradually and cook over boiling water until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks (with water); pour hot mixture over them gradually.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Just before removing from heat, add lemon juice and butter.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or oil baking sheet.
Pat each biscuit into a 4-inch circle and place on a baking sheet.
Mix the tomato sauce and oregano and spoon some on each biscuit.
Spoon the mushrooms over the tomato sauce.
Put a few slices of meat and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake about 8 minutes or until crust is light brown.

title: chicken breasts with pecan sausage stuffing
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles; remove sausage from pan, and set aside; discard drippings.

title: summertime tea(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice and combine all ingredients except vanilla in a large pan.
Bring to a boil until foam on top (white).
Cut heat to low. Cover pan and cook for approximately 1 hour, stirring often.
After rice is done, add vanilla.

title: old fashioned t cake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and buttermilk.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add Wesson oil and vanilla.
In a large bowl, sift flour like you would for biscuits.
Make hole in center of flour and pour part of liquid mixture in hole.
Mix like making biscuits, working in flour.
Add more liquid until you have used all the liquid.
Squeeze off small amount and roll out on floured board or wax paper to desired thickness and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Liquid mixture can be refrigerated and used later.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Fry meat and onion; drain.
Add rice and mix together.
Place chopped cabbage in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour meat and rice over it.
Mix soup, water and ketchup; pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
